:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=451453\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:585:\"<p>Are you looking for the best Google Analytics plugin for your WordPress site? Google Analytics helps you to track the visitors to your website and get detailed information about them. In this article, we&#8217;ll compare the best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress and help you to choose the best one for your needs. Do You [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-google-analytics-plugins-for-wordpress/\">7 Best Google Analytics Plugins for WordPress in 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Sandipan Mukherjee\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16167:\"<p>Are you looking for the best Google Analytics plugin for your WordPress site? Google Analytics helps you to track the visitors to your website and get detailed information about them. In this article, we&#8217;ll compare the best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress and help you to choose the best one for your needs.</p>\n<h3>Do You Need a Google Analytics Plugin?</h3>\n<p>Google Analytics is a free analytics tool and is useful for tracking the number of visitors that visit your website. Not only that, but you can:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Know the demographics of your visitors.</li>\n<li>See how people are finding your website.</li>\n<li>Check which pages on your site receive the maximum visits.</li>\n<li>Get real-time stats.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453043\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/google-analytics.png\" alt=\"Google Analytics\" width=\"562\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/google-analytics.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/google-analytics-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>To use Google Analytics, you&#8217;ll have to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">add a tracking code to your site</a>. This can be difficult for a lot of people unless they&#8217;re technically very confident.</p>\n<p>However, if you&#8217;re using WordPress, you can use a plugin to install the Google Analytics tracking code on your site. And some of the plugins even allow you to check the stats in your WordPress admin panel.</p>\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s get started with the list of the best Google Analytics plugins for WordPress.</p>\n<h3>1. <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453045\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/monsterinsights-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Plugin\" width=\"562\" height=\"187\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/monsterinsights-plugin.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/monsterinsights-plugin-300x100.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights is the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It allows you to set up Google Analytics to track your site traffic easily. And the good news is you don&#8217;t have to touch a single line of code.</p>\n<p>This plugin shows you detailed reports about your visitors including their country, gender, which device they&#8217;re using, and more. You can also check how they found your website, what keywords they searched for, who referred them, and even, what they did on your site.</p>\n<p>To see the site stats, you don&#8217;t have to go to the Google Analytics website. You can <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">check everything inside your WordPress dashboard</a>. Isn&#8217;t that cool?</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453060\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/check-site-stats-inside-wordpress-dashboard.png\" alt=\"check site stats inside WordPress dashboard\" width=\"562\" height=\"326\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/check-site-stats-inside-wordpress-dashboard.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/check-site-stats-inside-wordpress-dashboard-300x174.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights comes with a number of useful addons to make life easy for you.</p>\n<p>It provides the Forms addon which allows you to track your form views, submissions, and the form conversion rate.</p>\n<p>You can also use the EU Compliance addon to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-gdpr-agreement-field-to-your-sites-forms/\">make your site compliant with GDPR</a> (General Data Protection Regulation) and other EU (European Union) privacy regulations.</p>\n<p>Are you using WooCommerce, Easy Digital Downloads, or <a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> on your site? You can integrate Google Analytics eCommerce tracking with a single click using this plugin. And then, you can see important data including your conversion rate, transactions, and average order value.</p>\n<p>Some of the other features of this plugin include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Universal tracking to collect data from any device.</li>\n<li>File download tracking to find out the number of times a file was downloaded.</li>\n<li>Integrate with Facebook Instant Articles.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Overall, it&#8217;s a very powerful analytics WordPress plugin. So <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">get started with MonsterInsights today</a>!</p>\n<h3>2. <a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ExactMetrics</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453041\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/exactmetrics-plugin.png\" alt=\"ExactMetrics Plugin\" width=\"562\" height=\"263\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/exactmetrics-plugin.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/exactmetrics-plugin-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>With more than 1 million active installs, ExactMetrics is a popular and free Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It was formerly known as Google Analytics Dashboard for WordPress (GADWP).</p>\n<p>It allows you to track the visitors to your website and get the analytics reports in your WordPress dashboard. So you can view vital details like page views, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-increase-pageviews-and-reduce-bounce-rate-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">bounce rate</a>, mobile analytics stats, organic searches, and traffic from social media sites.</p>\n<p>You can also check the real-time stats including the number of visitors, traffic sources, and acquisition channels.</p>\n<p>This plugin provides in-depth reports for each page and post. Thus you can analyze the data and optimize your content to get better results.</p>\n<p>ExactMetrics makes it easy for you to track events like downloads, emails, affiliate links, and more. You can also enable tracking for AMP (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-properly-setup-google-amp-on-your-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Accelerated Mobile Pages</a>) if you want.</p>\n<h3>3. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-analytify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Analytify</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-analytify/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453039\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/analytify-plugin.png\" alt=\"Analytify plugin\" width=\"562\" height=\"246\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/analytify-plugin.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/analytify-plugin-300x131.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Analytify is a freemium Google Analytics plugin and offers simple installation process to add the tracking code to your site.</p>\n<p>Just like MonsterInsights, it lets you view the analytics reports inside your WordPress admin area. You can also check the statistics of individual posts, pages, and custom post types.</p>\n<p>This plugin offers different addons to enhance its functionality. For example, you can track campaigns using UTM (Urchin Tracking Module) parameters.</p>\n<p>Also, you can <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/woocommerce-conversion-tracking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">use eCommerce tracking for WooCommerce</a> and Easy Digital Downloads to get an overview of your sales, transactions, and revenues.</p>\n<p>Want to receive the reports in your email inbox? Analytify can send automated email reports for every post, page, or the general stats of your site.</p>\n<h3>4. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/enhanced-e-commerce-for-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics Plugin</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/enhanced-e-commerce-for-woocommerce-store/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453040\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enhanced-ecommerce-google-analytics-plugin-for-woocommerce.png\" alt=\"Enhanced eCommerce Google Analytics plugin for WooCommerce\" width=\"562\" height=\"184\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enhanced-ecommerce-google-analytics-plugin-for-woocommerce.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enhanced-ecommerce-google-analytics-plugin-for-woocommerce-300x98.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Looking for a Google Analytics plugin to track your WooCommerce store? Enhanced Ecommerce Google Analytics plugin is a <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-free-wordpress-plugins-for-your-website/\">free WordPress plugin</a> that&#8217;s suitable for your needs.</p>\n<p>It uses the eCommerce tracking feature of Google Analytics to study the user behavior and helps you to <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-optimization-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">optimize your online store</a> based on that data. And it supports 4 types of behavior and performance reports: shopping, checkout, product, and sales.</p>\n<p>This plugin helps you to capture product clicks, product impressions, and add to cart events on your product page, category page, featured product section, and more.</p>\n<p>However, this plugin comes with certain limitations. It doesn&#8217;t support product types other than simple products. Also, it&#8217;s not fully compatible with custom and child themes.</p>\n<h3>5. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wd-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Google Analytics by 10Web</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wd-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453044\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/google-analytics-by-10web.png\" alt=\"Google Analytics by 10Web\" width=\"562\" height=\"262\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/google-analytics-by-10web.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/google-analytics-by-10web-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Google Analytics by 10Web is another freemium plugin on our list.</p>\n<p>It allows you to set and manage goals within your WordPress admin area. Also, you can get all your analytics reports in your dashboard, just like MonsterInsights and ExactMetrics.</p>\n<p>This plugin allows you to integrate with Google Adsense and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-track-form-submissions-as-google-adwords-conversions/\">Google Ads</a> (formerly Google Adwords) to get important data that matters to you.</p>\n<p>Some of the other features of this plugin include <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-export-wordpress-form-entries-to-csv/\">export reports in CSV</a>, send automated email reports, eCommerce tracking, get custom notifications on specific triggers, and set custom tracking codes.</p>\n<h3>6. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ga-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GA Google Analytics</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/ga-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453042\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ga-google-analytics-plugin.png\" alt=\"GA Google Analytics Plugin\" width=\"562\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ga-google-analytics-plugin.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/ga-google-analytics-plugin-300x120.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>GA Google Analytics is a lightweight and GDPR compliant WordPress plugin. You can use this plugin to enable the tracking code on all the pages of your site.</p>\n<p>It allows you to disable tracking of admin-level users to get the right data. Also, you can easily customize the tracking code if you want.</p>\n<p>However, this plugin doesn&#8217;t display your site stats inside your admin panel. You&#8217;ll have to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-login-to-google-analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">log in to your Google Analytics account</a> to view the analytics data.</p>\n<p>Overall, GA Google Analytics is a basic plugin with limited functionality. And to get additional features, you&#8217;ll have to upgrade to the pro version of this plugin.</p>\n<h3>7. <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-google-analytics-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WP Google Analytics Events</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-google-analytics-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-453046\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wp-google-analytics-events.png\" alt=\"WP Google Analytics Events\" width=\"562\" height=\"181\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wp-google-analytics-events.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wp-google-analytics-events-300x97.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Want to track certain events on your site without writing any code? You can do that with the help of WP Google Analytics Events plugin.</p>\n<p>Google Analytics events can be useful for understanding what your visitors do on your website. For example, you can use events to compare the performance of your CTA (call to action) buttons. Or, it can be used to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-links-and-button-clicks-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">track links</a>, page navigation, and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-track-user-locations-with-wordpress-form-submissions/\">contact form submissions</a>.</p>\n<p>However, you should remember one thing: this plugin is not a typical Google Analytics plugin to track site stats and the demographics of your visitors.</p>\n<p>Anyways, WP Google Analytics Events plugin also comes with a premium version that offers extra features including YouTube and Vimeo tracking. It also offers premium support and 30 days money back guarantee.</p>\n<h3>Final Thoughts on the Best Google Analytics Plugins</h3>\n<p>After comparing the above plugins, we can conclude that <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a> is the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It offers tons of useful features and allows you to view the reports in your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>In case you&#8217;re looking for a free option, we can highly recommend <a href=\"https://exactmetrics.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ExactMetrics</a> to you.</p>\n<p>Anyways, we hope this article helped you to select the best Google Analytics plugin for your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for an easy way to track the form conversions on your WordPress website, then check out our step by step tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-track-wordpress-form-conversions-step-by-step/\">how to track WordPress form conversions</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, please follow us on <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> to get updates from our blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-google-analytics-plugins-for-wordpress/\">7 Best Google Analytics Plugins for WordPress in 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wpforms.com/best-google-analytics-plugins-for-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"How to Connect Your WordPress Contact Form to Discord\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-connect-your-wordpress-contact-form-to-discord/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-connect-your-wordpress-contact-form-to-discord/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 30 Apr 2019 12:00:53 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"contact form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"zapier\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPForms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"zapier addon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=444226\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:599:\"<p>Are you wondering how to integrate Discord with your contact form? Discord allows you to text and voice chat with other gamers while you&#8217;re playing your favorite game. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to connect your WordPress contact form to Discord. How to Connect WordPress Form to Discord? Discord is a free text [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-connect-your-wordpress-contact-form-to-discord/\">How to Connect Your WordPress Contact Form to Discord</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Sandipan Mukherjee\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17665:\"<p>Are you wondering how to integrate Discord with your contact form? Discord allows you to text and voice chat with other gamers while you&#8217;re playing your favorite game. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to connect your WordPress contact form to Discord.</p>\n<h3>How to Connect WordPress Form to Discord?</h3>\n<p>Discord is a free text and voice chat app for gamers. It works on every device including your phone and desktop. You can use it to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Allow people to join your Discord channel.</li>\n<li>Host gaming tournaments and invite gamers to participate in it.</li>\n<li>Connect with like-minded people.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To allow people to join your Discord server, you can <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">start a WordPress website</a> and add a contact form to your site. And then, you&#8217;ve to connect your form to your Discord server.</p>\n<p>Thus, whenever someone submits the form, an automatic message will be sent to your Discord channel. And later you can invite them to your server.</p>\n<p>So let&#8217;s show you to the step by step process of connecting your WordPress contact form to Discord.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Create a WordPress Form</h3>\n<p>The first thing you need to do is install and activate <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">WPForms plugin</a>. It&#8217;s the best drag and drop form builder plugin that allows you to create different types of forms without any hassle.</p>\n<p>You can follow the guide on <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a> if you need any help.</p>\n<p>Now, you can always use <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">a simple contact form</a> for this tutorial. However, let&#8217;s create a gaming tournament registration form assuming that you&#8217;re planning to host a gaming tournament.</p>\n<p>And for that, you need to install the <strong>Form Templates Pack</strong> addon.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-446972\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-form-templates-pack-addon.png\" alt=\"install Form Templates Pack addon\" width=\"562\" height=\"215\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-form-templates-pack-addon.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-form-templates-pack-addon-300x115.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Form Templates Pack addon comes with more than 100 pre-built form templates for almost every niche. To install this addon, go to <strong>WPForms</strong> » <strong>Addons </strong>and click on the <strong>Install Addon</strong> button once you find it.</p>\n<p>Now go to <strong>WPForms</strong> » <strong>Add New</strong> to create a new form. Search for the gaming tournament form in the <strong>Additional Templates</strong> section and click on it to use the template.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-446977\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/additional-templates.png\" alt=\"additional templates\" width=\"562\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/additional-templates.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/additional-templates-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>With WPForms, you can customize your form easily and that too without any coding skills. You can add or remove fields and even reorder them by merely dragging and dropping the fields.</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done with the design part, you can <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-notification-wpforms/\">change the notification</a> and other settings of this form. Finally, save the form using the <strong>Save</strong> button present in the top-right corner.</p>\n<p>Want to check out our form? Here&#8217;s the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/demo/gaming-tournament-registration-form-demo/\">gaming tournament form demo</a>.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Add a Test Entry to Your Form</h3>\n<p>You&#8217;ll have to add at least one entry to your form to test the connection between Discord and WPForms. This will be required in the later stage of this tutorial.</p>\n<p>To create a new entry, you can embed your form to any post, page, or even the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-sidebar-widget/\">sidebar of your website</a>.</p>\n<p>But let&#8217;s use the preview option and create one test entry. So go to <strong>WPForms » All Forms</strong>, hover the mouse cursor over the title of your form and click on the <strong>Preview</strong> option.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-446993\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/preview-form.png\" alt=\"preview form\" width=\"562\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/preview-form.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/preview-form-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Once your form opens in a new page, fill in the form and click on the <strong>Submit</strong> button to create a new entry for testing purpose.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s move to the next step now.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Install Zapier Addon</h3>\n<p>We&#8217;ll be using <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/zapier-addon/\">Zapier addon</a> to connect our WordPress form to Discord. So go to <strong>WPForms</strong> » <strong>Addons</strong> and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/install-activate-wpforms-addons/\">install the Zapier addon</a>.</p>\n<p>For those who don&#8217;t know, Zapier allows you to integrate your form to over 1300 apps and do various tasks easily.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447009\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/zapier-addon.png\" alt=\"zapier addon\" width=\"562\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/zapier-addon.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/zapier-addon-300x120.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, go to <strong>WPForms</strong> » <strong>Settings</strong> and click on the <strong>Integration</strong> tab.</p>\n<p>Here you&#8217;ll see the Zapier API key for your site. You&#8217;ll need this API key to connect your WPForms site to Zapier. So keep this page open and proceed to the next step.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447225\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-zapier-integration-api-key.png\" alt=\"WPForms Zapier integration api key\" width=\"562\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-zapier-integration-api-key.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-zapier-integration-api-key-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3>Step 4: Create a New Zap</h3>\n<p>Zapier allows you to connect two or more apps to do automated tasks. This process is called Zap. It requires a trigger to do a particular action.</p>\n<p>In our case, the trigger is when someone submits the form and the action is a message will be posted in the Discord channel of your choice.</p>\n<p>To create a new Zap, go to the Zapier website and log in to your account. If you don&#8217;t have a Zapier account, you can <a href=\"https://zapier.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">create a new account</a> for free.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447027\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/make-a-zap.png\" alt=\"make a zap\" width=\"562\" height=\"234\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/make-a-zap.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/make-a-zap-300x125.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Now click on the <strong>Make a Zap!</strong> button present in the top-right corner of your screen. This will open up a new page where we&#8217;ll be selecting WPForms as our trigger app.</p>\n<p>You can use the <strong>Choose a Trigger App</strong> search box to find WPForms. Once you find it, click on it to go to the next step.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447033\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-a-trigger-app.png\" alt=\"choose a trigger app\" width=\"562\" height=\"145\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-a-trigger-app.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-a-trigger-app-300x77.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>WPForms offers just one trigger option. So select the trigger option <strong>New Form Entry</strong> and click on <strong>Save + Continue</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447038\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/new-form-entry.png\" alt=\"new form entry\" width=\"562\" height=\"258\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/new-form-entry.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/new-form-entry-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>In the next step, you&#8217;ll have to connect your WPForms account to Zapier. To do that, click on the <strong>Connect an Account</strong> button.</p>\n<p>This will open up a popup window. Here you&#8217;ve to enter your full website URL and the Zapier API key. You can go back to step 3 to understand how to get your API key.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447044\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/allow-access-to-zapier.png\" alt=\"allow access to Zapier\" width=\"562\" height=\"482\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/allow-access-to-zapier.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/allow-access-to-zapier-300x257.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Once done, click on <strong>Yes, Continue</strong> button to connect your website to Zapier.</p>\n<p>Now you&#8217;ll be taken back to the configuration wizard where you&#8217;ll see your WPForms account. You can click on the <strong>Test</strong> button to check if your website is connected or not.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447061\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/test-connection.png\" alt=\"test connection\" width=\"562\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/test-connection.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/test-connection-300x171.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>If you get a success message, then click on <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to go to the next step.</p>\n<p>Zapier will now fetch all your website forms and ask you to select one from the dropdown box. Select the Gaming Tournament Registration form that you&#8217;ve created earlier and click <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447063\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-form-from-dropdown.png\" alt=\"select form from dropdown\" width=\"562\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-form-from-dropdown.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-form-from-dropdown-300x114.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, Zapier will show you all the entries of your gaming tournament form. Just select any one of the entries for testing purpose and then click on <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 5: Choose Discord as an Action App</h3>\n<p>In the last step, you&#8217;ve successfully created your trigger app. It&#8217;s time to choose Discord as the action app.</p>\n<p>So search for <strong>Discord</strong> and click on it to continue.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447067\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-an-action-app.png\" alt=\"choose an action app\" width=\"562\" height=\"140\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-an-action-app.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-an-action-app-300x75.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>In the next step, you&#8217;ll be asked to select a Discord action that you want to happen when your form is submitted.</p>\n<p>Since you want a message to be posted to your Discord channel, select <strong>Send Channel Message</strong> and click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447070\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-discord-action.png\" alt=\"select Discord action\" width=\"562\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-discord-action.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-discord-action-300x186.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>You need to connect your Discord server to Zapier now. To do this, click on <strong>Connect an Account</strong>.</p>\n<p>A popup window will open up asking you to select a Discord server from the dropdown menu. And then, you&#8217;ve to click on the <strong>Authorize</strong> button to give Zapier the permission to use your Discord account.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447079\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/authorize-discord-app.png\" alt=\"authorize discord app\" width=\"562\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/authorize-discord-app.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/authorize-discord-app-300x214.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>After this, you need to click on the Google reCaptcha box to prove that you&#8217;re not a robot. Once done, your Discord account will be added to Zapier.</p>\n<p>You can check the connection by clicking on the <strong>Test</strong> button. Once you get the success message, click on <strong>Save + Continue</strong> to proceed to the next step.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447146\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/test-discord-connection.png\" alt=\"test Discord connection\" width=\"562\" height=\"234\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/test-discord-connection.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/test-discord-connection-300x125.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you&#8217;ll have to set up the Discord channel message template. Don&#8217;t worry! It&#8217;s very simple.</p>\n<p>First of all, select a Discord channel from the <strong>Channel</strong> dropdown box. This will be the channel where all the form entries will be posted automatically.</p>\n<p>The <strong>Message Text</strong> box allows you to decide what message you want to be posted on your channel when someone submits the contact form on your site.</p>\n<p>You can click on the <strong>Insert a Field</strong> icon to add the contact form fields to the text area. And you can also add custom text if you want.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447197\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/discord-channel-message-template.png\" alt=\"discord channel message template\" width=\"562\" height=\"425\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/discord-channel-message-template.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/discord-channel-message-template-300x227.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Rest of the fields are optional. So scroll down to the bottom of the form and click on <strong>Continue</strong>.</p>\n<p>To test whether everything is working properly, you can click on <strong>Send Test to Discord</strong> button in the next step. You&#8217;ll receive a success message saying that your test message was sent to Discord. You can also confirm that by checking your Discord channel.</p>\n<p>Now click on <strong>Finish</strong> to complete the action setup process and go to the final step.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-447211\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-to-discord-zap.png\" alt=\"WPForms to Discord Zap\" width=\"562\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-to-discord-zap.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-to-discord-zap-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Lastly, give any name to your Zap and turn it to <strong>ON </strong>to make your WPForms to Discord zap start working.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! You&#8217;ve successfully connected your WPForms contact form to Discord. So whenever someone submits the form, a message will be sent to your Discord channel automatically.</p>\n<h3>Endnote</h3>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to understand how to connect your WordPress form to Discord.</p>\n<p>If you want to add events to Google Calendar from your WordPress form, please check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-send-wpforms-entries-to-google-calendar/\">how to send WPForms entries to Google Calendar</a>.</p>\n<p>Not using WPForms so far? Get started with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">best WordPress form plugin</a> today!</p>\n<p>If you liked this article, please follow us on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> to get updates from our blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-connect-your-wordpress-contact-form-to-discord/\">How to Connect Your WordPress Contact Form to Discord</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-connect-your-wordpress-contact-form-to-discord/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"5 Mailchimp Alternatives That Are More Powerful (+Better Support)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://wpforms.com/mailchimp-alternatives/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wpforms.com/mailchimp-alternatives/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 29 Apr 2019 12:00:07 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"form conversion rate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"mailchimp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"newsletter\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"email opt-in\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"email marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=440550\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:609:\"<p>Are you looking for Mailchimp alternatives for your email marketing software? Building an email list and using email marketing is so important for a successful online business. In this article, we&#8217;ll take a look at Mailchimp alternatives that are more powerful and offer better support. Therefore, you can make sure you&#8217;re using the email marketing [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/mailchimp-alternatives/\">5 Mailchimp Alternatives That Are More Powerful (+Better Support)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22362:\"<p>Are you looking for Mailchimp alternatives for your email marketing software?</p>\n<p>Building an email list and using email marketing is so important for a successful online business.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll take a look at Mailchimp alternatives that are more powerful and offer better support. Therefore, you can make sure you&#8217;re using the email marketing service that&#8217;s right for your business.</p>\n<h3>What Are the Best Mailchimp Alternatives?</h3>\n<p>Here are 5 of the best Mailchimp alternatives:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong><a title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/convertkit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ConvertKit</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"SendInBlue\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SendInBlue</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GetResponse</a></strong></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Is Mailchimp Any Good?</h3>\n<p>Mailchimp is easily one of the most well-known email marketing providers around. A lot of people use Mailchimp because it has a free version where you can build an email list with up to 2,000 subscribers.</p>\n<p>Like most email marketing platforms, Mailchimp can help you with landing pages, monitoring your email campaigns, and providing Facebook ad templates.</p>\n<p>In addition, it has detailed reports where you can view real-time stats and check out how well your emails are doing.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448130\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/mailchimp-reporting-dashboard.jpg\" alt=\"mailchimp-reporting-dashboard\" width=\"562\" height=\"283\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/mailchimp-reporting-dashboard.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/mailchimp-reporting-dashboard-300x151.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Also, Mailchimp has a cool feature where you can schedule your email delivery time.</p>\n<p>For instance, you can use this to send at the time of day that most people open emails. The same email can be sent at separate times to different subscribers based on their location. This helps <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/7-ways-to-boost-your-email-marketing-click-rate/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">increase click-through rates</a>.</p>\n<p>Even though there are some great benefits of Mailchimp, it&#8217;s not for everyone. Especially if you&#8217;re a small business owner looking for a more powerful option and better support.</p>\n<h3>Mailchimp Alternatives</h3>\n<p>If you&#8217;re thinking about using something besides Mailchimp, you have tons of great options.</p>\n<p>So, here are some of the best Mailchimp alternatives:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Constant Contact (Better Support)</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-434673 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-logo.jpg\" alt=\"constant-contact-logo\" width=\"562\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-logo.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-logo-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> is going to be a solid choice if you&#8217;re looking for a Mailchimp alternative that has better support.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s one of the fastest growing email marketing providers around. Also, it&#8217;s crazy simple to use which makes it perfect for small business owners with lots to do.</p>\n<p>On top of that, Constant Contact is the email marketing service that comes already built-in to the WPForms plugin. You can easily <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-constant-contact-checkbox-to-your-contact-form/\">add a Constant Contact checkbox</a> to any WordPress form on your site.</p>\n<p>But their support is what really makes Constant Contact great. They&#8217;re known across the email marketing industry as having the best customer support.</p>\n<p>So, what makes Constant Contact&#8217;s support so fantastic?</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448135\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-help.jpg\" alt=\"constant-contact-help\" width=\"562\" height=\"494\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-help.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-help-300x264.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>To start, it&#8217;s easy to access and has lots of documentation. Including written and video tutorials.</p>\n<p>Plus, they offer weekend help, phone support, live chat, and how-to&#8217;s. The live chat is available in multiple languages so International customers can get help, too.</p>\n<p>Also, they have the always active and extremely helpful Constant Contact Community, with more than half a million registered users.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448145\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-community.png\" alt=\"constant-contact-community\" width=\"562\" height=\"248\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-community.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-community-300x132.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>This type of A+ support is super important if you want your email marketing to be as easy and effective as possible.</p>\n<p>For instance, not all small businesses are the same and owners or entrepreneurs often don&#8217;t work traditional hours and days. With Constant Contact&#8217;s support, <a title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">you&#8217;re always going to have help when you need it</a>. That way, you can focus more of your energy on building your business.</p>\n<p>Some of the other amazing features that make Constant Contact a fantastic Mailchimp alternative:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A simple drag and drop builder</li>\n<li>100+ pre-designed email templates</li>\n<li>Automatically send personalized emails to visitors based on their behavior</li>\n<li>Built-in heat tracking lets you see exactly where your readers are clicking</li>\n<li>Segmentation options based on the user&#8217;s behavior on your website</li>\n<li>Keep track of bounces, inactive emails, marked as spam, and unsubscribers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cost: </strong>Constant Contact has plans that start at $20/month for unlimited emails and up to 500 subscribers.</p>\n<p>Also, they offer a 60-day free trial and it doesn’t require a credit card.</p>\n<p>So if you&#8217;re looking for Mailchimp alternatives that offer better support, then you&#8217;ll definitely want to get started with <a title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> today.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Drip (More Powerful)</strong></p>\n<p><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-434675\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drip-logo.jpg\" alt=\"drip-logo\" width=\"562\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drip-logo.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drip-logo-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a> is going to be your best bet if you&#8217;re looking for Mailchimp alternatives that are more powerful.</p>\n<p>Of course, this user friendly email marketing service is integrated with WPForms. Check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-drip-signup-form-in-wordpress-updated/\">how to setup Drip with your WPForms</a>. It only takes a few steps.</p>\n<p>So, what makes Drip so powerful? One reason is because it offers the unique feature of automated customer workflows that trigger specific actions. Including split testing workflows.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448155\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/split-test-workflow.jpg\" alt=\"split-test-workflow\" width=\"562\" height=\"311\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/split-test-workflow.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/split-test-workflow-300x166.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Sounds powerful? It is. Drip is more than just an email marketing provider. The service is technically an eCommerce Customer Relationship Manager (ECRM).</p>\n<p>You might recognize the term CRM because of popular CRM tools like <a title=\"HubSpot\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hubspot/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">HubSpot</a>, Salesforce, or Zoho. As you may know if you&#8217;ve ever used them, those tools are all very powerful and have tons of features.</p>\n<p>But Drip focuses on eCommerce customers, and therefore email marketing. It&#8217;s truly an incredible marketing automation platform.</p>\n<p>In fact, <a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip is the first ECRM in the world</a>, which is pretty cool. As an ECRM, their software has a lot of really powerful features you won&#8217;t find in an email marketing software like Mailchimp.</p>\n<p>Just because the tools are more powerful doesn&#8217;t mean it&#8217;s not easy to use, either. In other words, it&#8217;s great for beginners. Plus, it has a sleek and modern interface.</p>\n<p>There are tons of great features that makes Drip a more powerful Mailchimp alternative like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Intuitive visual workflow builder for automation workflows</li>\n<li>Connects with Facebook Lead Ads and Custom Audiences</li>\n<li>10 built-in reports on your WordPress dashboard with easy export</li>\n<li>Sends texts</li>\n<li>A/B testing to find out when/how your users engage with your messages</li>\n<li>Split testing workflows</li>\n<li>Landing page integrations</li>\n<li>Advanced subscriber management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cost: </strong>Drip users are on a paid plan. They don&#8217;t have a free plan. The Basic option starts at $45/month for unlimited emails and up to 2,500 subscribers.</p>\n<p>In addition, there&#8217;s a 14-days trial available.</p>\n<p>So if you want a Mailchimp alternative that&#8217;s more powerful and has email automation, you should be using <a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>3. ConvertKit (More Powerful)</strong></p>\n<p><a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/convertkit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-440591\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/convertkit-logo.jpg\" alt=\"convertkit-logo\" width=\"562\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/convertkit-logo.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/convertkit-logo-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/convertkit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ConvertKit</a> is another powerful email service provider to think about. Especially if extra tools and ease of use are important to you in your search for Mailchimp alternatives.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s a favorite of many bloggers. Also, it has email marketing automation workflows to help you send your email automatically, and it does the job very well.</p>\n<p>Plus, ConvertKit makes <a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/convertkit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">email marketing easy to understand and use.</a> That&#8217;s great if you&#8217;re looking for a very easy software.</p>\n<p>For instance, you can easily build signup forms or landing pages that have custom fields and are <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-gdpr-compliant-forms/\">GDPR compliant.</a></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448165\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-a-template-convertkit.jpg\" alt=\"choose-a-template-convertkit\" width=\"562\" height=\"267\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-a-template-convertkit.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/choose-a-template-convertkit-300x143.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Plus, it&#8217;s simple to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-customized-convertkit-form-in-wordpress/\">setup ConvertKit in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<p>Here are more of the notable features you can expect from ConvertKit:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Drag and drop email editor to make personalized emails</li>\n<li>Supports <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">lead magnets to increase subscribers</a></li>\n<li>A user friendly interface and dashboard</li>\n<li>Segmentation options by tagging users based on interests</li>\n<li>Powerful funnels to automatically personalize a user&#8217;s path based on their actions</li>\n<li>Plain text option to prevent your email from being missed in the spam folder</li>\n<li>Allows for double opt-ins to reduce spam</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cost: </strong>ConvertKit has paid plans that start at $29/month for unlimited emails and up to 1,000 subscribers.</p>\n<p>You can also sign up for a free 14-day trial to make sure it’s the right email service software for you.</p>\n<p>So if you need a Mailchimp alternative that&#8217;s super simple to use and also has powerful email automation features, you should give <a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/convertkit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ConvertKit </a>a try.</p>\n<p><strong>4. SendInBlue (More Than Email)</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-377107\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/sendinblue.png\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/sendinblue.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/sendinblue-300x172.png 300w\" alt=\"sendinblue\" width=\"562\" height=\"322\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"SendInBlue\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SendInBlue</a> is going to be a great choice if you&#8217;re looking for Mailchimp alternatives that offer more of an all-in-one email marketing service. That&#8217;s because it connects with people by texts, too.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s a strong player in the email marketing software industry because it helps you build stronger relationships with your users by both email and text (SMS) marketing.</p>\n<p>SendInBlue is user friendly and simple. Plus, you can use SendInBlue with WPForms.</p>\n<p>The drag and drop email editor helps you draft and build personalized emails to send to your email list.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448168\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drag-and-drop-designer-sendinblue.jpg\" alt=\"drag-and-drop-designer-sendinblue\" width=\"562\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drag-and-drop-designer-sendinblue.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drag-and-drop-designer-sendinblue-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Additionally, you&#8217;ll have access an HTML editor.</p>\n<p>Here are some other cool things <a title=\"SendInBlue\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SendInBlue</a> has:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Insightful and detailed reports with heat mapping features</li>\n<li>Automated workflows</li>\n<li>A/B testing to research different ways to get better conversions</li>\n<li>Easy to use text messaging</li>\n<li>A lead scoring system that ranks your leads so you can focus on the most important leads in your funnel</li>\n<li>Mobile-friendly, responsive templates</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cost: </strong>A paid plan with SendInBlue starts at $25/month for 40,000 emails a month and has unlimited subscribers.</p>\n<p>It does have a free plan that lets you send up to 300 emails/day and have unlimited subscribers.</p>\n<p>So if you&#8217;re wanting Mailchimp alternatives that focus on customer relationship building with email and SMS, you&#8217;ll love <a title=\"SendInBlue\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SendInBlue</a>.</p>\n<p><b>5. GetResponse (All-In-One)</b></p>\n<p><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-325567\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/getresponse-logo.jpg\" alt=\"getresponse logo\" width=\"562\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/getresponse-logo.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/getresponse-logo-300x172.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GetResponse</a> is a good pick if you&#8217;re looking for Mailchimp alternatives and want to have a simple email marketing solution that also offers powerful CRM tools.</p>\n<p>Plus, you can easily build a bigger email list with GetResponse since you can <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-getresponse-signup-checkbox-to-your-contact-form/\">add a GetResponse checkbox to your contact form in WPForms.</a></p>\n<p>GetResponse lets you send automated emails, create HTML newsletters, and monitor statistics. Plus, it has list segmentation options.</p>\n<p>Also, GetResponse has the very unique feature to host webinars. Webinars are a popular way to generate online leads.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-448179\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/get-response-webinars.jpg\" alt=\"get-response-webinars\" width=\"562\" height=\"287\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/get-response-webinars.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/get-response-webinars-300x153.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Check out this great article on <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/webinar-marketing-101-how-to-sell-anything-with-webinars/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">webinar marketing 101</a> on our sister site to learn more.</p>\n<p>Other GetResponse features include:</p>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>Landing page builder to increase sales</li>\n<li>A/B testing great for small business owners with no prior email marketing experience</li>\n<li>Personalized emails based on visitor behavior</li>\n<li>Tags to organize your campaigns</li>\n<li>Modern interface with a drag and drop builder</li>\n<li>CRM functionality</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Cost: </strong><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GetResponse</a> paid plans start at $15/month for unlimited emails and 1,000 subscribers.</p>\n<p>Additionally, you can sign up for a 30-day free trial to see exactly how the GetResponse works.</p>\n<p>So if an all-in-one email marketing software with a CRM is a must-have on your search for Mailchimp alternatives, you should use <a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GetResponse</a>.</p>\n<h3>Final Thoughts</h3>\n</div>\n<p>Finding the best Mailchimp alternatives for your needs depends on your industry, budget and goals. To review, our favorite Mailchimp alternatives are:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>Constant Contact</strong></a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>Drip</strong></a></li>\n<li><a title=\"ConvertKit\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/convertkit/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>ConvertKit</strong></a></li>\n<li><a title=\"SendInBlue\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/sendinblue/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>SendInBlue</strong></a></li>\n<li><a title=\"GetResponse\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/getresponse-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>GetResponse</strong></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Keep in mind, not all features come with the cheapest plans for these email marketing programs. The number of emails you need to send per day or the emails per month are important things to think about, too. You&#8217;ll need to pick for yourself what fits your business best.</p>\n<p>That wraps it up! You now know which Mailchimp alternatives are more powerful and have better support.</p>\n<div>\n<p>Once you decide which email marketing service is the best option for you, you’ll want to <a href=\"http://wpforms.com/why-you-should-start-building-an-email-list\">start building an email list right away</a>.</p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for? Get started turning site visitors into subscribers with the most powerful <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>And don&#8217;t forget, if you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/mailchimp-alternatives/\">5 Mailchimp Alternatives That Are More Powerful (+Better Support)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"https://wpforms.com/mailchimp-alternatives/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"How to Securely Send WordPress Emails Using Gmail SMTP with WP Mail SMTP\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-securely-send-wordpress-emails-using-gmail-smtp/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-securely-send-wordpress-emails-using-gmail-smtp/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 25 Apr 2019 20:02:10 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"smtp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"form notification\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"notifications\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=35577\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:611:\"<p>Looking for a secure SMTP plugin that helps you receive email notifications from your WordPress contact forms? With WP Mail SMTP, you can fix delivery issues by authenticating emails through your Gmail or G Suite account &#8212; all while keeping your login credentials safe. In this post, we’ll show you how to set up WP [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-securely-send-wordpress-emails-using-gmail-smtp/\">How to Securely Send WordPress Emails Using Gmail SMTP with WP Mail SMTP</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Shahzad Saeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26676:\"<p>Looking for a secure SMTP plugin that helps you receive email notifications from your WordPress contact forms? With WP Mail SMTP, you can fix delivery issues by authenticating emails through your Gmail or G Suite account &#8212; all while keeping your login credentials safe. </p>\n<p>In this post, we’ll show you how to set up WP Mail SMTP for sending WordPress emails with your Gmail or G Suite email address.</p>\n<h3>Why You’re Not Receiving Notifications</h3>\n<p>By default, WordPress uses the <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/php/\" target=\"_blank\">PHP</a> mail function to send emails generated by WordPress or any contact plugin like <a href=\"http://wpforms.com/\">WPForms</a>.  The most common reason for not getting emails is that your WordPress hosting server is not configured to use PHP mail function.</p>\n<p>In addition to this, anti-spam efforts by email providers can impact your emails as well. As part of their filtering process, many email providers will check whether your email originates from the same domain noted in the From Email. For example, if your email claims to be sent from your Gmail address but is actually sent from your website&#8217;s server (rather than Gmail&#8217;s server), your email may be sent to spam or not be delivered at all.</p>\n<p>You can fix this by using SMTP instead of the PHP mail function. SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol) is the industry standard for sending emails reliably.</p>\n<h3>Why Use the WP Mail SMTP Plugin?</h3>\n<p>The main benefit of using the WP Mail SMTP plugin is that it lets you send WordPress emails securely using your Gmail or G Suite account without requiring to enable less secure apps in your account.</p>\n<p>In addition, unlike many other SMTP options, you won’t need to enter your Gmail username and password in your WordPress dashboard where other site users can see them. By using this method, you&#8217;ll help to <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Ultimate Guide to WordPress Security\">keep your WordPress site secure</a>.</p>\n<p>Let’s take a look at how to set up WP Mail SMTP for sending WordPress emails.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install the WP Mail SMTP Plugin</h3>\n<p>The first thing you need to do is to install and activate the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-mail-smtp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">WP Mail SMTP</a> plugin. For step-by-step instructions, you can check out <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\">WPBeginner&#8217;s guide on how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>After installing and activating WP Mail SMTP, go to <strong>Settings » WP Mail SMTP</strong> to open the plugin settings page. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Open-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings-page-1.png\" alt=\"Open WP Mail SMTP settings page\" width=\"450\" height=\"309\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423553\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Open-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings-page-1.png 450w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Open-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings-page-1-300x206.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\" /></p>\n<p>At the top of this page, you&#8217;ll see the <strong>From Email</strong> and <strong>From Name</strong>. You can ignore these settings, because Google will automatically force these values to match the email account used in the next step.</p>\n<p>To start the setup process, you&#8217;ll need to scroll to the <strong>Mailer</strong> field and select the <strong>Google</strong> option.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Select-Google-mailer-option-in-WP-Mail-SMTP-1.png\" alt=\"Select Google mailer option in WP Mail SMTP\" width=\"562\" height=\"214\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423571\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Select-Google-mailer-option-in-WP-Mail-SMTP-1.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Select-Google-mailer-option-in-WP-Mail-SMTP-1-300x114.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\"><p><strong>Note:</strong> Google&#8217;s API (used by the Google mailer) will not allow you to customize certain aspects of your emails, such as the Reply To email address. If this is an important option in your project, please consider using <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-fix-wordpress-contact-form-not-sending-email-with-smtp/\" title=\"How to Fix WordPress Contact Form Not Sending Email With SMTP\">an alternative mailer option</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<p>You can skip the <strong>Return Path</strong> checkbox, as Google does not allow this setting to be altered.</p>\n<p>Next, you should see a new Gmail section appear. Here, you&#8217;ll see fields for <strong>Client Secret</strong> and <strong>Client ID</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-section-of-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings.png\" alt=\"Gmail section of WP Mail SMTP settings\" width=\"562\" height=\"359\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423589\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-section-of-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-section-of-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings-300x192.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>To get the information for these fields, you&#8217;ll need to create a web application through your Google account. This doesn&#8217;t require any coding, and we&#8217;ll show you exactly what to do.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Create a Web Application</h3>\n<p>To create an application, you&#8217;ll first need to <a href=\"https://console.developers.google.com/flows/enableapi?apiid=gmail&#038;pli=1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">sign into your Gmail account and access Gmail&#8217;s application registration</a>. Clicking that link should open this Google page in a new tab or window, and you&#8217;ll want to keep your site settings open (we&#8217;ll return to those later).</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve followed that link and logged into your Gmail account, you should see a form named &#8220;Register your application for Gmail API in Google API Console&#8221;. </p>\n<p>In the dropdown labeled <strong>Select a project where your application will be registered</strong>, leave the default option of <strong>Create a project</strong>. In some cases, you may also be asked to agree to terms of service.</p>\n<p>After filling out this form, go ahead and click the <strong>Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Create-a-new-project-for-Google-application.jpg\" alt=\"Create a new project for Google application\" width=\"562\" height=\"323\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423633\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Create-a-new-project-for-Google-application.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Create-a-new-project-for-Google-application-300x172.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you should see a screen that says &#8220;The API is enabled&#8221;. To proceed to the setup page, click the <strong>Go to credentials</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-API-is-enabled.png\" alt=\"Gmail API is enabled\" width=\"500\" height=\"205\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423593\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-API-is-enabled.png 500w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-API-is-enabled-300x123.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p>In the next page, you’ll be prompted to determine the credentials you need. Here are the fields on this page and the options you&#8217;ll need to select:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Which API are you using?</strong> Gmail API</li>\n<li><strong>Where will you be calling the API from?</strong> Web server (e.g. node.js, Tomcat)</li>\n<li><strong>What data will you be accessing?</strong> User data</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve made these selections, click the <strong>What credentials do I need?</strong> button to go to the next step.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Add-credentials-to-Gmail-app-project.png\" alt=\"Add credentials to Gmail app project\" width=\"500\" height=\"513\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423600\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Add-credentials-to-Gmail-app-project.png 500w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Add-credentials-to-Gmail-app-project-292x300.png 292w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></p>\n<p>After clicking this button, Google will show a popup asking you to set up a consent screen. Go ahead and click on the <strong>Set Up Consent Screen Option</strong>. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Open-OAuth-consent-screen.png\" alt=\"Open OAuth consent screen\" width=\"562\" height=\"279\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-422938\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Open-OAuth-consent-screen.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Open-OAuth-consent-screen-300x149.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>This will open a new tab or window. Be sure to keep the original tab/window open, as we&#8217;ll return to it a little later.</p>\n<p>In the new tab/window, you&#8217;ll be asked for several details to prepare your consent screen. This is the permissions screen that will display to you later in the setup process (never seen by your users).</p>\n<p>If you have a G Suite account, you&#8217;ll first set <strong>Application type</strong> to <strong>Internal</strong>. You will not see this option if you&#8217;re using an @gmail.com email account.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Select-internal-application-type.jpg\" alt=\"Select internal application type\" width=\"562\" height=\"381\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423628\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Select-internal-application-type.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Select-internal-application-type-300x203.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>For <strong>Application name,</strong> you can add the name of your website (or any other name that feels logical to you).</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Fill-in-app-details.png\" alt=\"Fill in app details\" width=\"562\" height=\"365\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-422941\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Fill-in-app-details.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Fill-in-app-details-300x195.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, you can skip down to <strong>Authorized domains</strong> and add the URL for your website. Be sure to not include <code>http://</code> or <code>https://</code> here.</p>\n<p>For <strong>Application Homepage link</strong>, <strong>Application Privacy Policy link</strong>, and <strong>Application Terms of Service link</strong>, you can again just add your website URL. You don&#8217;t need to have special privacy or terms pages in place for this app, as again this consent screen will only ever be seen by you.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Add-authorized-domain-information-to-Google-consent.png\" alt=\"Add authorized domain information to Google consent\" width=\"588\" height=\"562\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423477\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Add-authorized-domain-information-to-Google-consent.png 588w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Add-authorized-domain-information-to-Google-consent-300x287.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 588px) 100vw, 588px\" /></p>\n<p>When you&#8217;re ready, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom of this screen.</p>\n<p>After saving your consent screen settings, Google will take you back to an API credentials screen. You can ignore this, and instead return to the first tab/window. </p>\n<p>For this step, you&#8217;ll be creating an OAuth client ID. OAuth, or Open Authorization, is what will provide permission for your website to use your Gmail account to authenticate emails.</p>\n<p>For the <strong>Name</strong> field, enter anything you like or leave the default name. This is only for reference within your Google account.</p>\n<p>For <strong>Authorized JavaScript origins</strong>, you&#8217;ll need to enter your site&#8217;s URL.</p>\n<p>Last, we need to fill out the <strong>Authorized redirect URIs</strong> field. To get the URI for your site, you&#8217;ll need to go back to the tab or window with your WordPress site. Still on the <strong>Settings &raquo; WP Mail SMTP</strong> page, you&#8217;ll need to look under the Gmail section for the field labeled <strong>Authorized redirect URI</strong>.</p>\n<p>The value in this field should be your site&#8217;s URL followed by some extra details. You&#8217;ll need to copy this value, which is easily done by clicking the button with the copy icon. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Use-button-to-copy-authorized-redirect-URI-from-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings.png\" alt=\"Use button to copy authorized redirect URI from WP Mail SMTP settings\" width=\"562\" height=\"134\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423641\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Use-button-to-copy-authorized-redirect-URI-from-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Use-button-to-copy-authorized-redirect-URI-from-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings-300x72.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>After copying the URI, return to the Google APIs page and paste it into the field under <strong>Authorized redirect URIs</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Create-OAuth-client-ID.png\" alt=\"Create OAuth client ID\" width=\"562\" height=\"633\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423481\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Create-OAuth-client-ID.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Create-OAuth-client-ID-266x300.png 266w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>When you finish filling out these details, you may see a <strong>Refresh</strong> button near the bottom of the page. Go ahead and click this.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-Refresh-button.png\" alt=\"Click Refresh button\" width=\"437\" height=\"267\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423519\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-Refresh-button.png 437w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-Refresh-button-300x183.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 437px) 100vw, 437px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you can click the <strong>Create client ID</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-blue-button-to-create-OAuth-client-ID.png\" alt=\"Click blue button to create OAuth client ID\" width=\"386\" height=\"264\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423522\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-blue-button-to-create-OAuth-client-ID.png 386w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-blue-button-to-create-OAuth-client-ID-300x205.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 386px) 100vw, 386px\" /></p>\n<p>You’ve now successfully created a Google web application!</p>\n<p>Now we need to see the full details. On the last screen, click <strong>I’ll do this later</strong> to go to the Credentials page.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-Ill-do-this-later.png\" alt=\"Click Ill do this later\" width=\"462\" height=\"496\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423524\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-Ill-do-this-later.png 462w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-Ill-do-this-later-279x300.png 279w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 462px) 100vw, 462px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"step-3\">Step 3: Grant Permissions and Send Test Email</h3>\n<p>On the Credentials page, you can now see the details of the web application you just created. To view <strong>Client ID</strong> and <strong>Client Secret</strong>, click the pencil icon.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-pencil-icon-to-see-details.png\" alt=\"Click pencil icon to see details\" width=\"562\" height=\"100\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423506\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-pencil-icon-to-see-details.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Click-pencil-icon-to-see-details-300x53.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>This will open all of the details for your app. On this page, you&#8217;ll see the <strong>Client ID</strong> and <strong>Client secret</strong> values.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Copy-Client-ID-and-Client-secret.png\" alt=\"Copy Client ID and Client secret\" width=\"562\" height=\"299\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423510\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Copy-Client-ID-and-Client-secret.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Copy-Client-ID-and-Client-secret-300x160.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Each of these will need to be copied into your WP Mail SMTP settings back in your WordPress admin screen.</p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\"><p><strong>Note:</strong> Be very careful not to copy any extra text or spaces with your Client ID or Client Secret, as this will result in an error in the next step.</p>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Copy-in-Client-ID-and-secret-to-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings.png\" alt=\"Copy in Client ID and secret to WP Mail SMTP settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"243\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-118086\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Copy-in-Client-ID-and-secret-to-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings.png 620w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Copy-in-Client-ID-and-secret-to-WP-Mail-SMTP-settings-300x118.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After saving these settings, the page will refresh. Before Google allows this information to be used to connect to your account, however, you must grant permission. </p>\n<p>To do this, scroll to the bottom of this page and click the button labeled <strong>Allow plugin to send emails using your Google account</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Authorize-plugin-to-send-emails-with-Gmail.png\" alt=\"Authorize plugin to send emails with Gmail\" width=\"562\" height=\"178\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423617\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Authorize-plugin-to-send-emails-with-Gmail.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Authorize-plugin-to-send-emails-with-Gmail-300x95.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>This will open a login screen for Google. Go ahead and log into the account you&#8217;re setting this SMTP up with. Then, you&#8217;ll see a screen asking for permission for this site to send email on your behalf. </p>\n<p>When you&#8217;re ready, click the <strong>Allow</strong> button to proceed.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Provide-permissions-to-your-Google-app.png\" alt=\"Provide permissions to your Google app\" width=\"462\" height=\"574\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423529\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Provide-permissions-to-your-Google-app.png 462w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Provide-permissions-to-your-Google-app-241x300.png 241w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 462px) 100vw, 462px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll be returned to your WP Mail SMTP settings and a success message will be displayed. Now that the connection is complete, you&#8217;re ready to send a test email under the <strong>Email Test</strong> tab.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-connection-success-with-WP-Mail-SMTP.png\" alt=\"Gmail connection success with WP Mail SMTP\" width=\"562\" height=\"290\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423625\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-connection-success-with-WP-Mail-SMTP.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Gmail-connection-success-with-WP-Mail-SMTP-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Once the Test Email tab is open, you&#8217;ll need to enter a valid email address and click the <strong>Send Email</strong> button. Be sure to use an email address you have access to so you can confirm the email is delivered.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Send-a-test-email-through-WP-Mail-SMTP.png\" alt=\"Send a test email through WP Mail SMTP\" width=\"430\" height=\"360\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-118145\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Send-a-test-email-through-WP-Mail-SMTP.png 430w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Send-a-test-email-through-WP-Mail-SMTP-300x251.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 430px) 100vw, 430px\" /></p>\n<p>When the test message has been sent, you&#8217;ll see a success message at the top of this tab.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/WP-Mail-SMTP-test-email-was-sent-successfully.png\" alt=\"WP Mail SMTP test email was sent successfully\" width=\"292\" height=\"274\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-118113\" /></p>\n<p>You should also soon receive a test email at the email address you entered.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Test-email-for-WP-Mail-SMTP-Gmail.png\" alt=\"Test email for WP Mail SMTP Gmail\" width=\"562\" height=\"431\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-423663\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Test-email-for-WP-Mail-SMTP-Gmail.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Test-email-for-WP-Mail-SMTP-Gmail-300x230.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n<h6>What If the Test Email Doesn&#8217;t Send Successfully?</h6>\n<p>If the SMTP test email isn&#8217;t able to send, a debug log will appear with additional details. Here are some of the possible error messages and how to resolve them.</p>\n<p><strong>401. That’s an error.<br />\nError: invalid_client</strong><br />\nThis error appears when the Client ID isn&#8217;t able to be read properly. To fix, try copying the Client ID in again and check that there&#8217;s no whitespace or extra text.</p>\n<p><strong>400. That’s an error.<br />\nError: invalid_request<br />\nMissing required parameter: client_id</strong><br />\nThis error will display when the Client ID field is empty or not able to be read properly. To fix, copy in the Client ID again and be careful to not add extra text or whitespace.</p>\n<p><strong>cURL error 60: SSL certificate problem</strong><br />\nThis message means that the server is missing a certificate that’s required for SMTP to work. To fix, you&#8217;ll need to contact your site&#8217;s hosting provider to ask them to install this certificate (most likely the cacert.pem certificate, though it&#8217;s best to ask your host to check).</p>\n<p><strong>“code”: 401,<br />\n“message”: “Login Required”</strong><br />\nIf you see this in the debug message, permission still needs to be granted to your use Google account. For instructions on how to fix this, please see <a href=\"#step-3\" title=\"Step 3: Grant Permissions and Send Test Email\">Step 3</a> of this tutorial. Also, be sure to check that the From Email in your SMTP settings matches the email used to setup the Google app.</p>\n<h6 id=\"verified\">What If I See a Screen Saying &#8220;This app isn&#8217;t verified&#8221;?</h6>\n<p>When you click the <strong>Allow plugin to send emails using your Google account</strong> button, Google might display a screen that says &#8220;This app isn&#8217;t verified. This app hasn&#8217;t been verified by Google yet. Only proceed if you know and trust the developer.&#8221; There&#8217;s no need to worry, though &#8212; the message is only referring to the app that you just created in your own Google account (so you are actually the developer in this case).</p>\n<p>To bypass this message, you&#8217;ll need click <strong>Advanced</strong> and then <strong>Proceed</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/This-app-isnt-verified-error.png\" alt=\"This app isnt verified error\" width=\"562\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-456979\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/This-app-isnt-verified-error.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/This-app-isnt-verified-error-300x160.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h6>What If I Want to Switch to A Different Email Later?</h6>\n<p>If you&#8217;d like to change to a different Gmail/G Suite email address, you&#8217;ll need to repeat all tutorial steps above. This includes generating a new Client ID and Client Secret under this other email account.</p>\n<p>When you get to the Authorization step (under Step 3), save your settings and then click the <strong>Remove Connection</strong> button. This will remove the authorization for your original email account and allow you to repeat the authorization steps with the new email.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Remove-connection-in-WP-Mail-SMTP.png\" alt=\"Remove connection in WP Mail SMTP\" width=\"703\" height=\"124\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-223847\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Remove-connection-in-WP-Mail-SMTP.png 703w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Remove-connection-in-WP-Mail-SMTP-300x53.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 703px) 100vw, 703px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s it! You’ve successfully configured WP Mail SMTP&#8217;s Google mailer on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>If you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook </a>and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Twitter</a> for more free WordPress tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-securely-send-wordpress-emails-using-gmail-smtp/\">How to Securely Send WordPress Emails Using Gmail SMTP with WP Mail SMTP</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-securely-send-wordpress-emails-using-gmail-smtp/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"843\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"39 WPForms Power Hacks To Grow Your Business Online\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 25 Apr 2019 12:00:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"zapier\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"lead generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"email marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPForms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=449358\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:603:\"<p>Looking for how to grow your business online and convert more of your site visitors into customers? Although WordPress forms may seem like basic necessities to your website, successful digital marketers know that forms are much more than a simple way for users to contact you. If you&#8217;re not taking advantage of all that WPForms has to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/\">39 WPForms Power Hacks To Grow Your Business Online</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68129:\"<p>Looking for how to grow your business online and convert more of your site visitors into customers? Although WordPress forms may seem like basic necessities to your website, successful digital marketers know that forms are much more than a simple way for users to contact you.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re not taking advantage of all that <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a> has to offer yet, you could be missing out on a lot of income.</p>\n<p>So whether you&#8217;re looking to boost your revenue or simply get website visitors to return to your site, here&#8217;s a list of effective WPForms power hacks to help you grow your business online.</p>\n<h3>1. Use Conditional Logic to Ask the Right Questions</h3>\n<p>You can easily show or hide something to a website visitor on your forms once they select something that triggers this.</p>\n<p>With Smart Conditional Logic, you can customize forms by having fields automatically show or hide other fields depending on a user’s selection.</p>\n<p>For instance, you may want to invite someone to write a review only if they give you a high rating on a <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-survey-form-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\">survey form</a>.</p>\n<p>Or, set up an extra field to appear when someone selects &#8216;Other&#8217; in your form. In that case, you&#8217;d show another field.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-450814 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conditional-logic-show-fields.gif\" alt=\"conditional-logic-show-fields-grow-your-online-business\" width=\"562\" height=\"322\" /></p>\n<p>On the other hand, it may be beneficial to hide fields. For example, maybe you only need one way to contact your users: an email address or a phone number. Once they start filling out their email address, you can set the phone field to be hidden automatically, and vice versa.</p>\n<p>You can even take it a step further with creating multiple conditions by using AND/OR logic.</p>\n<p>And it&#8217;s much easier than you may think. Check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-use-conditional-logic-with-wpforms/\">how to use conditional logic with WPForms.</a></p>\n<h3>2. Send Form Notifications to the Right People</h3>\n<p>With Conditional Notifications, you can send out different emails to different people / departments depending on what a user selects on your form.</p>\n<p>For example, if a user is submitting a complaint and selects that they had an issue with billing, you could have an email go out to a billing coordinator from your team.</p>\n<p>If the same users selects that their issue was with sales, you could direct that email to come to you or whoever manages sales for your small business.</p>\n<p>Head over to our step by step instructions on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-conditional-form-notifications-in-wpforms/\">how to create conditional form notification emails in WPForms</a> to learn more.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-450862\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/notification-conditional-logic.jpg\" alt=\"notification-conditional-logic\" width=\"562\" height=\"171\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/notification-conditional-logic.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/notification-conditional-logic-300x91.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>All of this is completely customizable and helps streamline your business processes so you can get back to customers more quickly.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-450864\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/notification-info-conditional.jpg\" alt=\"notification-info-conditional\" width=\"562\" height=\"315\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/notification-info-conditional.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/notification-info-conditional-300x168.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>So that way, you can keep visitors happy and turn them into loyal fans who spend money, send referrals, and help grow your business online.</p>\n<h3>3. Display Custom Messages Based on User Actions</h3>\n<p>This hack lets you decide what people see after they hit the submit on your form, and it changes based on their previous actions.</p>\n<p>You can apply conditional rules to trigger different things to take place when someone submits to your form including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Display a Message. </strong>Add a Thank You note after a customer makes a purchase or donates to your cause, then provide them with next steps.</li>\n<li><strong>Redirect Users to a Page on Your Website. </strong>Show visitors different web pages based on which product they purchase.</li>\n<li><strong>Send Users to an Entirely Different URL. </strong>Redirect users to an external website if they show interest in an affiliate product you asked about in a survey form.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And these confirmations are really easy to setup and edit.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-450868\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/add-new-conditional-confirmation.jpg\" alt=\"add-new-conditional-confirmation\" width=\"562\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/add-new-conditional-confirmation.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/add-new-conditional-confirmation-300x186.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>So start customizing your forms today and choose what happens to each user when they submit by reading <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-conditional-form-confirmations/\">how to create conditional form confirmations.</a></p>\n<h3>4. Get More Leads with Partial Form Submissions</h3>\n<p>Would you like to get more leads without increasing your website traffic? That&#8217;s easy with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-abandonment-addon/\">Form Abandonment Addon</a>.</p>\n<p>This may come as a surprise to you, but most visitors stop filling out forms before they hit submit.</p>\n<p>In fact, a staggering <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/online-form-statistics-facts/\">81% of people have abandoned a form after beginning to fill it out</a>.</p>\n<p>And once they&#8217;re gone, they may forget to come ever back and complete the form. Just think about those 8 out of 10 website visitors who <strong>almost</strong> sent you their information, but you missed out on.</p>\n<p>Form abandonment is one of the biggest challenges you need to tackle to grow your business online, and the Form Abandonment Addon will help you.</p>\n<p>This is a great hack for capture those partial entries as leads anyway. Using the Form Abandonment Addon, you can save partial form submissions and follow up with those interested prospects with an abandonment email, even if they didn&#8217;t complete the entire form. This is a smart way to invite them back to complete the form so they don&#8217;t forget about you.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451359\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms.jpg\" alt=\"Abandoned Forms Example\" width=\"562\" height=\"445\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Entry-status-for-abandoned-and-completed-forms-300x238.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Check out our guide on how to install and use the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-form-abandonment-with-wpforms\">Form Abandonment Addon with WPForms</a> so you can uncover way more leads from your forms than you&#8217;ve been getting. You may be shocked about how many visitors who didn&#8217;t finish submitting to your form end up converting to paying customers!</p>\n<h3>5. Create Multi-Column Layouts With a Click</h3>\n<p>A nifty power hack to try out on your WPForms is customizing your form&#8217;s appearance with multi-column layouts.</p>\n<p>By default, your forms display fields in one column. With multi-column layout, each field has a layout setting that lets you customize how your fields are displayed.</p>\n<p>Choice layouts let you do this inside the multiple choice field. With the multiple choice field, you can select 1, 2, or 3 columns to display your choices inside of.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-450906\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-column-layout.jpg\" alt=\"select-column-layout\" width=\"562\" height=\"242\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-column-layout.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/select-column-layout-300x129.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-multi-column-form-layouts-in-wpforms/\">how to create multi-column form layouts in WPForms</a>. This hack helps keep your forms looking great so more people fill them out and you can continue to grow your business online. Plus, it&#8217;s especially helpful if you&#8217;ve got a lot of questions but want to keep them all on one page.</p>\n<p>So keep in mind, nobody loves filling out long forms. Our next hack has you covered to prevent that.</p>\n<h3>6. Use Multi-Page Forms to Boost Completion Rates</h3>\n<p>Sometimes, your forms need to collect a lot of information.</p>\n<p>In this case, use the easy drag and drop builder to break long forms into multi-page forms and improve the user&#8217;s experience.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451721\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/multi-page-forms.jpg\" alt=\"multi-page-forms\" width=\"562\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/multi-page-forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/multi-page-forms-300x154.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Plus, people are more likely to complete your forms if they are broken up into bite-sized pieces. It&#8217;s just easier to fill out.</p>\n<p>There are lots of times multi-page forms are helpful. Here are some of the most popular uses:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>WordPress Multi-Page <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-user-registration-form-in-wordpress/\">Registration Forms</a></strong>. If you’re looking to have users register for something, then this form can be very handy.</li>\n<li><strong>Multi-Page <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-job-application-form-in-wordpress/\">Job Application Forms</a>.</strong> Hiring is an important process. Multi-Page forms make it easy for you to collect all the data you need.</li>\n<li><strong>Multi-Page Patient Data Forms.</strong> Do you have a medical practice? Offer massage services? Multi-Page forms make it easy for you to collect and store all the patient information that you need.</li>\n<li><strong>Multi-Step Payment <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-order-form-in-wordpress/\">Order Forms</a>.</strong> Payment orders sometimes require more information. Break it down in multiple steps to create a smooth process.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We walk you through setting this up in <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-multi-page-forms-in-wpforms/\">how to create Multi-Page forms in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<h3>7. Customize Breadcrumbs for Multi-Page Forms</h3>\n<p>Already using a multi-page form? Try this hack:</p>\n<p>Change the look of your Multi-Page Forms by customizing the <strong>Progress Indicator</strong>, also known as Breadcrumbs. These Breadcrumbs keep the users informed about their progress as they progress through filling out a multi-page form.</p>\n<p>And WPForms offer 3 different types of breadcrumb layouts for you to choose from for your forms:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Progress Bar</li>\n<li>Circles</li>\n<li>Connector</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here are examples of each style of Progress Indicator in action:</p>\n<p><strong>Progress Bar</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451365\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Progress-Bar-Progress-Indicator-Example.jpg\" alt=\"Progress-Bar-Progress-Indicator-Example\" width=\"562\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Progress-Bar-Progress-Indicator-Example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Progress-Bar-Progress-Indicator-Example-300x107.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Circles</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451368\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Circles-Progress-Indicator-Example.jpg\" alt=\"Circles-Progress-Indicator-Example\" width=\"562\" height=\"217\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Circles-Progress-Indicator-Example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Circles-Progress-Indicator-Example-300x116.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Connector</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451369\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Connector-Progress-Indicator-Example.jpg\" alt=\"Connector-Progress-Indicator-Example\" width=\"562\" height=\"188\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Connector-Progress-Indicator-Example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Connector-Progress-Indicator-Example-300x100.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Plus, you can even change the color to keep the branding of your website consistent. We chose green in the examples above, but you can choose whatever color you want.</p>\n<p>Check out our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-multi-page-forms-in-wpforms/\">how to create multi-page forms in WPForms</a> for more details on customizing Breadcrumbs.</p>\n<h3>8. Setup Zapier to Connect with 500+ Apps</h3>\n<p>You can do so many truly amazing things with the power of Zapier + WPForms!</p>\n<p>This hack lets you add even more integration options to your forms.</p>\n<p>Zapier is a connector service that helps you integrate to tons of web applications. This lets you supercharge the functionality of your forms and get more done, faster.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451381\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/zapier-with-wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"zapier-with-wpforms\" width=\"562\" height=\"580\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/zapier-with-wpforms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/zapier-with-wpforms-291x300.jpg 291w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Some of the 500+ integrations help your forms automatically do things like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/the-easy-way-to-capture-leads-from-wordpress-to-salesforce/\">Create a Lead in Salesforce</a></li>\n<li>Make Invoices in FreshBooks</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-contact-in-hubspot-from-a-wordpress-form/\">Create a Contact in HubSpot</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-get-an-sms-text-message-from-your-wordpress-form/\">Send Text Messages Using Twilio</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-automatically-add-a-google-contact-from-your-wordpress-forms/\">Add a Google Contact</a></li>\n<li>Make a Task in Basecamp, <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-automatically-create-trello-cards-from-your-wordpress-forms/\">Trello</a> or <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-automatically-create-an-asana-task-from-a-wordpress-form/\">Asana</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-automatically-add-a-quickbooks-customer-from-your-wordpress-forms-2/\">Add a Customer in QuickBooks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-get-slack-notifications-from-your-wordpress-forms/\">Get a Slack Notification</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Plus, it requires zero coding knowledge to integrate WPForms with Zapier.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-451392 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/integrate-zapier-with-wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"integrate-zapier-with-wpforms-grow-your-online-business\" width=\"562\" height=\"431\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/integrate-zapier-with-wpforms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/integrate-zapier-with-wpforms-300x230.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And we&#8217;ve got your setup covered in <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-zapier-addon-with-wpforms/\">how to install and user the Zapier Addon in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<h3>9. Make Your Form Interactive &amp; Easier to Complete</h3>\n<p>You can create interactive forms by using Conversational Forms. This is a really powerful hack to grow your business online because it&#8217;s effective <strong>and</strong> beautiful.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451414\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-forms-example-survey.gif\" alt=\"conversational-forms-example-survey\" width=\"562\" height=\"405\" /></p>\n<p>Conversational Forms by WPForms makes your forms feel more human. It&#8217;s interactive because it asks people for their info one question at a time, much like a face-to-face conversation.</p>\n<p>Plus, it&#8217;s the first true interactive form layout built exclusively for WordPress that&#8217;s <strong>guaranteed to boost form completion</strong> and conversions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"btn btn-block\" style=\"background-color: #659a17 !important; color: #fff !important; padding: 20px 25px !important; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px !important; -moz-border-radius: 4px !important; -webkit-border-radius: 4px !important; font-weight: bold;\" title=\"Click Here to See a Conversational Form Demo\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/conversational-forms-demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click Here to See a Conversational Form Demo</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>WPForms is an affordable Typeform alternative that can be used for many things including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a title=\"Surveys and Polls Addon\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/surveys-and-polls-addon/\">Survey Forms</a>.</strong> Instead of overwhelming visitors with tons of questions, use the Conversational Forms’ one question at a time approach to improve your survey completion rate.</li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"How to Create a Job Application Form in WordPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-job-application-form-in-wordpress/\">Job Application Form</a>.</strong> 60% of <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/online-form-statistics-facts/\">job seekers abandon the job application forms</a> because they’re too long or complicated. With conversational forms, you can make your job application forms easy.</li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/demo/event-planner-form-demo/\">Event Planning Form</a>.</strong> Are you planning an event? You know how many questions you have to ask clients to plan the perfect event. The step by step, one question at a time approach gets you the data you need without tiring your clients.</li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"User Registration Addon\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/user-registration-addon/\">User Registration Form.</a></strong> Use conversational forms to improve your registration form conversion rate.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And you can try Conversational Forms out today without needing to create any new forms. You can turn any of your existing WordPress forms into an interactive form with a click of a button. Check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-conversational-forms-addon/\">how to install and use the Conversational Forms Addon</a>.</p>\n<h3>10. Create Distraction-Free Landing Pages for Focus</h3>\n<p>The biggest reason why people abandon your website without filling out your form is distraction.</p>\n<p>Use the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-pages-addon/\">Form Pages Addon</a> to create completely customized and distraction-free landing pages to boost your conversions.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451424\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/landing-form-pages-example.jpg\" alt=\"Click Here to See Form Pages Demo\" width=\"562\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/landing-form-pages-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/landing-form-pages-example-300x224.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Most WordPress themes don&#8217;t prioritize your form layouts. In other words, your themes control the layouts.</p>\n<p>But that&#8217;s not the case if you use the Form Pages by WPForms to create custom landing pages. You get to take control of your landing page layouts with Form Pages.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451427\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-pages-settings.jpg\" alt=\"form-pages-settings\" width=\"562\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-pages-settings.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-pages-settings-300x226.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Form Pages by WPForms gives you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Quick and easy setup (No coding required)</li>\n<li>Custom logo support</li>\n<li>Multiple styles to choose from</li>\n<li>Premade and custom color schemes</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"btn btn-block\" style=\"background-color: #659a17 !important; color: #fff !important; padding: 20px 25px !important; line-height: 48px; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px !important; -moz-border-radius: 4px !important; -webkit-border-radius: 4px !important; font-weight: bold;\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/form-pages-demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click Here to See Form Pages Demo</a></p>\n<p>Reducing distractions for your website visitors is one of the most popular hacks to grow your business online, build your email list, and avoid form abandonment.</p>\n<p>To learn more, head over to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-form-pages-addon/\">how to install and use the Form Pages Addon</a>.</p>\n<h3>11. Use a Pre-Built Form for Easy 1-Click Setup</h3>\n<p>Try using the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-templates-pack-addon/\">Form Templates Pack Addon</a> as a quick and simple hack to setup an already fully functioning and ready-to-go form.</p>\n<p>There are tons of options for templates available.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451431\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-template-pack-addon-additional-templates.jpg\" alt=\"form-template-pack-addon-additional-templates\" width=\"562\" height=\"406\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-template-pack-addon-additional-templates.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-template-pack-addon-additional-templates-300x217.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>With just one click, you can import a form demo from nearly every niche and industry, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Alumni Donation Form</li>\n<li>Avon Order Form</li>\n<li>Auction Item Registration Form</li>\n<li>Baseball League Registration Form</li>\n<li>Equipment Checkout Form</li>\n<li>Girl Scout Cookie Order Form</li>\n<li>High School Reunion Registration Form</li>\n<li>Performance Improvement Plan Form</li>\n<li>Sponsorship Request Form</li>\n<li>Summer Camp Registration Form</li>\n<li>Volunteer Recruitment Form</li>\n<li>Webinar Registration Form</li>\n<li>Wedding Invitation RSVP Form</li>\n<li>Much more&#8230;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And it takes very little time to set this up. To learn how, head over to our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-form-templates-pack-addon/\">how to install and use the Form Templates Pack Addon.</a></p>\n<h3>12. Use a Password to Protect Your Forms</h3>\n<p>Use this hack get better data from your forms.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking to increase the overall quality of your form submissions, set up a password to make sure only visitors with that password can submit to your form. This can be done by using the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-locker-addon/\">Form Locker Addon</a>.</p>\n<p>You may want to do this for a lot of reasons, including collecting reviews, success stories, or if you&#8217;re accepting guest posts on your blog but only want to get submissions from people who have the password. That way, you won&#8217;t get as many low-quality submissions because people who know what you&#8217;re looking for will have the password.</p>\n<p>For instance, you can give out a password through an email campaign sent to users based on a specific purchase, or at the bottom of a special web page listing your guest blogging rules.</p>\n<p>Best of all, you can enable password protection for your forms and create your password in just a few steps.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-290579\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/password-settings.png\" alt=\"password settings\" width=\"562\" height=\"495\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/password-settings.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/password-settings-300x264.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Take a look at <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-password-protect-wordpress-forms-step-by-step/\">how to password protect your forms</a> to set this power hack up now.</p>\n<p>Head over to our article with more <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/user-generated-content-examples/\">user generated content examples to save time and grow your business</a>.</p>\n<h3>13. Close Forms on a Set Date/Time Automatically</h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-locker-addon/\">Form Locker Addon</a> has tons of helpful hacks inside of it, including the ability to close forms at a specific date and time.</p>\n<p>This is a great tool for things like job applications or any other time-sensitive forms, and it&#8217;s a fantastic feature to try if you&#8217;re looking for how to grow your business online.</p>\n<p>And you can set this up easily by editing the Scheduling for your forms inside of the Form Locker.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451437\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/close-contest-certain-date-time-1.jpg\" alt=\"close-contest-certain-date-time\" width=\"562\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/close-contest-certain-date-time-1.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/close-contest-certain-date-time-1-300x274.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>For exact details on how to do this, check out our step by step article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-form-locker-addon-in-wpforms/\">how to install and use the Form Locker Addon in WPForms.</a></p>\n<h3>14. Close Forms After a Set Number of Entries</h3>\n<p>Another magic hack to try with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-locker-addon/\">Form Locker Addon</a> is the Entry Limit option. This caps the number of total entries and closes the form when that set number is reached.</p>\n<p>For example, you may be running a contest that accepts the first 100 submissions. After that, the form will automatically close. When this happens, you can invite users to sign up for a newsletter to find out how to enter next month’s contest.</p>\n<p>And people love contests, so this is a great hack to grow your business online while limiting the total entries to each contest. Learn more in our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-limit-the-number-of-wordpress-form-entries/\">how to limit the number of WordPress form entries.</a></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451441\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-entry-limit-example-closed.jpg\" alt=\"form-entry-limit-example-closed\" width=\"562\" height=\"515\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-entry-limit-example-closed.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-entry-limit-example-closed-300x275.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3>15. Limit 1 Entry per Person to Avoid Multiple Entries</h3>\n<p>Another awesome hack to try with WPForms is limiting one entry per person on your forms. This is another one of the many effective hacks you can use with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-locker-addon/\">Form Locker Addon</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451444\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-locker-settings-location.jpg\" alt=\"form-locker-settings-location\" width=\"562\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-locker-settings-location.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-locker-settings-location-300x178.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>When you limit your forms to one entry per person, you can avoid duplicate submissions. And this is really useful for scholarship applications, giveaways, and more.</p>\n<p>The tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-limit-the-number-of-wordpress-form-entries/\">how to limit the number of WordPress form entries</a> has details on exactly how to cap your forms at one entry per person.</p>\n<h3>16. Restrict Forms so Only Members Can Submit</h3>\n<p>One of the coolest power hacks available in the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-locker-addon/\">Form Locker Addon</a> is the ability to only allow members of your site to submit to a form.</p>\n<p>In other words, if you have a website that has registered users, you can allow only those that are logged in to submit to specific forms.</p>\n<p>Here are some examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You want to ask your website members questions, you might use a <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-survey-form-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\">survey</a> or <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/good-poll-questions-to-ask-on-your-forms-for-better-feedback/\">poll</a> form restricted to only those that are registered and logged in</li>\n<li>You’re hosting an event that&#8217;s only open to registered users and you&#8217;re using an <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-make-an-event-registration-form-in-wordpress/\">event registration form</a></li>\n<li>You&#8217;re hosting a webinar that doesn’t require registration but instead just a simple confirmation of attendance, so you <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-an-rsvp-form-in-wordpress/\">create an online RSVP form</a></li>\n<li>You want logged in users to be able to submit support requests about their experience, so you <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-support-ticket-form-template-best-practices/\">create a support ticket form</a> that only they can submit</li>\n<li>You’re running a contest that&#8217;s only open to those that have registered on your website</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451452\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-restriction-message.jpg\" alt=\"form-restriction-message\" width=\"562\" height=\"331\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-restriction-message.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-restriction-message-300x177.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Also, if you aren&#8217;t using the power of a membership area or site, <a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> is a great tool to check out for learning about, building, and managing a membership site.</p>\n<p>So if you want to set this hack up, read our step by step article on how to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-restrict-access-to-logged-in-users-on-your-wordpress-forms/\">restrict access to logged in users on your WordPress forms</a>.</p>\n<h3>17. Setup Payment Checkboxes to Sell Even More</h3>\n<p>Curious how to grow your business online fast with boosting your income by selling multiple items on your website at once?</p>\n<p>You can use the Payment Checkboxes hack. This lets users choose as many items as they’d like from any number of choices.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451461\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-checkboxes-example.jpg\" alt=\"payment-checkboxes-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"240\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-checkboxes-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-checkboxes-example-300x128.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Check out exactly how to do this in <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-choose-the-right-form-field-for-your-forms/\">how to choose the right form field for your forms</a>.</p>\n<p>And this hack is extra special because you can even add an image to each choice. That&#8217;s covered in our next hack.</p>\n<h3>18. Use Image Choice Fields for a Visual Checkout</h3>\n<p>If you&#8217;d like to make your forms super visual, consider adding images to your forms. This hack is especially helpful on order forms.</p>\n<p>WPForms makes it simple to add images to your Checkboxes, Multiple Choice, and items fields so your users can <strong>see</strong> the option or item you’ve listed. That way, they can make sure they are selecting exactly what they want!</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-450889\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/image-choice-fields.jpg\" alt=\"image-choice-fields\" width=\"562\" height=\"636\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/image-choice-fields.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/image-choice-fields-265x300.jpg 265w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And this guide will show you <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-add-image-choices-to-fields/\">how to add image choices to existing or new fields in WPForms.</a></p>\n<h3>19. Use Smart Tags to Add Info to Your Notifications</h3>\n<p>This is another powerful hack to grow your business online and to automatically add information to your form notifications.</p>\n<p>A Smart Tag is a bit of code you can use to insert relevant information to your <a title=\"How to Set Up Form Notifications in WPForms\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-notification-wpforms/\">form notification settings</a> or as field default values. Smart Tags use curly brackets and look something like this:<code>{admin_email}</code>.</p>\n<p>Smart Tags are great hacks because they can save you time by allowing you to include useful details in your forms.</p>\n<p>The <code>{admin_email}</code><strong> </strong>is the default Smart Tag used in the <strong>Send To Email Address</strong> field in forms. And it automatically fills in the email address of the site administrator.</p>\n<p>And there are tons of other ways to customize your notifications with Smart Tags, making getting detailed form submissions so much easier.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451462\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enhanced-notifications-with-smart-tags.jpg\" alt=\"enhanced-notifications-with-smart-tags\" width=\"562\" height=\"660\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enhanced-notifications-with-smart-tags.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enhanced-notifications-with-smart-tags-255x300.jpg 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Check out our instructions on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-use-smart-tags-in-wpforms/\">how to use Smart Tags in WPForms</a> to get started with this power hack right now.</p>\n<h3>20. Use Smart Tags in Hidden Fields to Uncover Data</h3>\n<p>Another smart hack to use in your arsenal is adding a Smart Tag to a Hidden Field on your form.</p>\n<p>For instance, by adding the {url_referer} Smart Tag, your form will automatically insert the address of the page which referred the user to the page containing the form. This will help you learn where on your site your website visitors are coming from before they end up on your form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451483\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hidden-field-smart-tags.jpg\" alt=\"hidden-field-smart-tags\" width=\"562\" height=\"558\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hidden-field-smart-tags.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hidden-field-smart-tags-150x150.jpg 150w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hidden-field-smart-tags-300x298.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hidden-field-smart-tags-100x100.jpg 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>For instance, if a user went from your home page to your contact page, and then filled out your form there, this Smart Tag would give you the URL of your home page.</p>\n<p>And you can also do this with IP addresses, geolocation, and more. This hack can help you learn a lot about your leads and help you convert them into paying customers. That way, you can grow your business online fast.</p>\n<p>Check out our step by step instructions on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-use-smart-tags-in-wpforms/#url\">how to use smart tags in hidden fields in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<h3>21. Respect GDPR Compliance + User Privacy</h3>\n<p>Are you trying to figure out how to grow your business online while also making sure your forms are also compliant with the European Union’s General Data Protection Regulation?</p>\n<p>Use this hack to make adjustments to your site and improve compliance with GDPR. You can change your form settings to <strong>Disable User Cookies,</strong> <strong>Disable User Details, </strong>and <strong>more.</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451488\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/gdpr-enhancement-features.jpg\" alt=\"gdpr-enhancement-features\" width=\"562\" height=\"504\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/gdpr-enhancement-features.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/gdpr-enhancement-features-300x269.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And enabling the GDPR-enhancement features within WPForms is really easy. Check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-gdpr-compliant-forms/\">how to create GDPR compliant forms</a>. For full details, please see this <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/the-ultimate-guide-to-wordpress-and-gdpr-compliance-everything-you-need-to-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ultimate guide to WordPress and GDPR</a>.</p>\n<h3>22. Use an Easy to Read + Scrollable Terms of Service</h3>\n<p>With rising privacy concerns, and the fact that privacy laws are getting more strict, we want to make it easy for you to comply and let your site visitors know their data is protected.</p>\n<p>Using the scrollable terms of service hack, you can make sure that adding your site’s privacy policy or terms of service doesn’t take away from the visual appeal of your form.</p>\n<p>If your ToS or privacy policy is too long, it could force site visitors to leave that page before they finish the form.</p>\n<p>Reduce form abandonment by adding a Terms of Service checkbox to your form and display it in a scrollable text box.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-166985\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/ToS-and-Disclaimer-Example.gif\" alt=\"ToS and Disclaimer Example\" width=\"562\" height=\"160\" /></p>\n<p>This makes sure your form isn’t bloated with text, and the information is visible to the user without having to leave the form page.</p>\n<p>And this hack makes your form way more user friendly, too.</p>\n<p>For step by step instructions, check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-add-disclaimer-terms-of-service-agreement-formatting/\">how to add disclaimer/terms of service agreement formatting</a> to your forms.</p>\n<h3>23. Try Custom Input Masks for Higher Quality Data</h3>\n<p>With WPForms, you can create your own custom input masks on your forms. In other words, you can customize the way data is entered into your WordPress forms. That way, you can grow your business online with more reliable data from your forms.</p>\n<p>This power hack is a fantastic way to improve user experience and ensure the correct data is entered into your form every single time.</p>\n<p>Here are some basic examples of input masks you can use in your WordPress forms.</p>\n<p><strong>United States Zip Code:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mask: 99999</li>\n<li>Example User Input: 89023</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Username with 6-8 Letters (first letter uppercase, the rest lowercase):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mask: Aaaaaa [aa]</li>\n<li>Example User Input: Minnie or Minniems</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Twitter Username with 4-15 Numbers or Uppercase/Lowercase Letters:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mask: @**** [***********]</li>\n<li>Example User Input: @easywpforms</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For help with using input mask symbols, check out this tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-use-custom-input-masks/#advanced\">adding input masks to your WordPress forms</a>.</p>\n<h3>24. Use Custom CAPTCHA to Prevent Spam</h3>\n<p>We know spam is a giant issue for contact forms. So, you can use the custom CAPTCHA feature as a hack to protect your forms from spam.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/custom-catpcha-addon/\">Custom Captcha Addon</a> lets you to set your own questions and answers to show your site visitors. Or, you can use this hack to add random math questions to make sure a user is a real human being. No one wants fake form submissions.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451508\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/custom-captcha-example.jpg\" alt=\"custom-captcha-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"125\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/custom-captcha-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/custom-captcha-example-300x67.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Head over to our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-custom-captcha-addon-in-wpforms/\">how to install and use custom captcha addon in WPForms</a> to set this up.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, if you&#8217;d prefer to use a simple checkbox, or even something invisible, our next hack is for you.</p>\n<h3>25. Setup Google reCAPTCHA v2 for Added Security</h3>\n<p>Using WPForms, and just a few steps, you can build spam-free WordPress contact forms. This hack is an excellent way to improve the quality of your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/lead-generation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">lead generation</a>.</p>\n<p>Remember all that jumbled text you used to have to squint to see and try to guess at? It wasn&#8217;t always easy to get form completions when users could become frustrated with guessing what those old captchas said on your forms.</p>\n<p>So these days, instead of entering text, users can just put their mouse over a checkbox and Google reCAPTCHA v2 understands that the users aren&#8217;t automated spam bots.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451526\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/recaptcha-in-form.jpg\" alt=\"recaptcha-in-form\" width=\"562\" height=\"518\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/recaptcha-in-form.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/recaptcha-in-form-300x277.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And you can also request a user doesn&#8217;t need to do anything to prove they are human by setting up Google v2&#8217;s invisible reCAPTCHA.</p>\n<p>Check out more details about setting up Google reCAPTCHA v2 in our <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-build-spam-free-wordpress-contact-forms-the-ultimate-guide/\">ultimate guide on how to build a spam-free WordPress contact form</a>.</p>\n<h3>26. Randomize Your Form Choices to Avoid Bias</h3>\n<p>Worried people are picking specific choices on your forms just because one is at the top? Maybe you&#8217;ve noticed a pattern where one answer is getting picked a lot. This could happen because of order bias.</p>\n<p>With WPForms, we&#8217;ve made it easy to avoid any sort of answer bias based on order.</p>\n<p>How? Well, there&#8217;s a super cool hack inside WPForms that lets you randomize the order of your fields each time your form is viewed by a visitor.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451540\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/randomize-choices-on-forms.jpg\" alt=\"randomize-choices-on-forms\" width=\"562\" height=\"510\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/randomize-choices-on-forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/randomize-choices-on-forms-300x272.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And this neat trick helps avoid any order bias, so it gathers more reliable data.</p>\n<p>So be sure to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-randomize-checkbox-and-multiple-choice-options/\">how to randomize checkbox and multiple choice options</a>.</p>\n<h3>27. Export and Re-Use Form Templates to Save Time</h3>\n<p>If you love the way one of your forms works and looks, you can export it and re-use it on another website you own.</p>\n<p>For example, say you&#8217;ve already created a custom form that started as form template, has your brand&#8217;s colors on the progress indicator bar, randomizes choices, and has reCAPTCHA enabled. But, you have another URL and website that you&#8217;d like to use this exact same form on and you don&#8217;t want to start from scratch.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451568\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/export-a-form.jpg\" alt=\"export-a-form\" width=\"562\" height=\"397\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/export-a-form.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/export-a-form-300x212.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t have to start over with your form. You can simply export and re-use it with all the features you&#8217;ve already created, saving you time and money as your grow your business online.</p>\n<p>So head over to our step by step article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-import-and-export-wpforms/#export-forms\">how to export forms</a> to learn more.</p>\n<h3>28. Add Bulk Multiple Choices to Create Forms Fast</h3>\n<p>Wouldn&#8217;t it be a great time-saver to be able to add a bunch of choices to your Multiple Choice fields all at once?</p>\n<p>With this nifty hack, you can!</p>\n<p>In other words, the Bulk Add option lets you quickly add a long list of items as options in your Multiple Choice fields.</p>\n<p>This works great if you&#8217;ve got a long list of products or departments and you&#8217;re asking your visitor to select just one.</p>\n<p>For example, say you&#8217;re collecting feedback through a form and want to know which department of your business the customer&#8217;s feedback is about.</p>\n<p>When you use the Bulk Add option in the Dropdown, Multiple Choice, and Checkboxes fields, it’s super simple to add a list of choices to your form all at once, instead of creating each choice individually.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451569\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Add-Bulk-Choices-to-Your-Forms.jpg\" alt=\"Add Bulk Choices to Your Forms\" width=\"562\" height=\"592\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Add-Bulk-Choices-to-Your-Forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Add-Bulk-Choices-to-Your-Forms-285x300.jpg 285w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>You can see exactly how to do this in our article <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-bulk-add-choices-for-multiple-choice-checkbox-and-dropdown-fields\">how to bulk add choices for multiple choice, checkbox and dropdown fields</a>.</p>\n<h3>29. Get More Content by Accepting Guest Posts</h3>\n<p>Accepting guest post submissions is a great hack to consistently get fresh content for your site. This way you can save your time and focus on other marketing tasks to grow your business.</p>\n<p>And the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/post-submissions-addon/\">WPForms Post Submissions Addon</a> makes it easy to collect user-submitted content in WordPress without users ever having to log in to your website&#8217;s admin area.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451587\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/post-submission-addon-active.jpg\" alt=\"post-submission-addon-active\" width=\"562\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/post-submission-addon-active.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/post-submission-addon-active-300x165.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>In other words, you can gather new content while <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">keeping your WordPress site secure</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451589\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/blog-post-submission-form-example.jpg\" alt=\"blog-post-submission-form-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"462\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/blog-post-submission-form-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/blog-post-submission-form-example-300x247.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Learn more in our step by step guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-post-submissions-addon-in-wpforms/\">how to install and use the Post Submissions Addon in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<h3>30. Allow WordPress Users to Register Themselves</h3>\n<p>Save yourself and your business a ton of time by letting people register for your website on their own.</p>\n<p>If you want to allow user registration on your WordPress site, you can quickly do this by creating a user registration form in WordPress that allows users to fill in the necessary information themselves.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451595\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Allow-WordPress-User-Registrations-1.jpg\" alt=\"Allow WordPress User Registrations\" width=\"562\" height=\"572\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Allow-WordPress-User-Registrations-1.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Allow-WordPress-User-Registrations-1-295x300.jpg 295w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>There are many benefits to creating a user registration form, but below are some popular reasons:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Organization.</strong> When you allow users to request access to your site, you&#8217;ve already collected all the important details needed to create their account.</li>\n<li><strong>Customization.</strong> You can control what information you need before someone creates an account, like requiring their website URL.</li>\n<li><strong>Security.</strong> By requiring new users to activate their setup via email, you can help <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/simple-tricks-to-eliminate-spam-user-registration/\">stop user registration spam</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Permissions.</strong> You can specify which level of access users will have on your site.</li>\n<li><strong>Membership Sites. </strong>You can create a membership site using one of the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-membership-plugins-compared/\">best WordPress membership plugins</a> on the market and require people register as a member using a registration form.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So get started on this power hack today. Here&#8217;s a step by step guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-user-registration-form-in-wordpress/\">how to create a user registration form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<h3>31. Use Branded Custom Login Forms for WordPress</h3>\n<p>A hack that a lot of super WPForms users use is customizing login forms. WPForms lets you easily make custom WordPress login forms for your website using our drag and drop form builder.</p>\n<p>Having a custom login page is a wonderful way to personalize the user experience while also further branding your business. You can set this hack up by making sure your <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/user-registration-addon/\">User Registration Addon</a> is active.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451598\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/WPForms-User-Registration-Addon.jpg\" alt=\"WPForms-User-Registration-Addon\" width=\"562\" height=\"171\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/WPForms-User-Registration-Addon.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/WPForms-User-Registration-Addon-300x91.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Some other popular reasons to create a custom login form include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ease of Access.</strong> You can <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-sidebar-widget/\">place the login form in a sidebar widget</a>, so that it’s easily visible and noticeable to users.</li>\n<li><strong>Security.</strong> Online forms are a huge target for spammers and bots. When you create a custom login page, you can hide the default login page. This will reduce login spam and help increase your site&#8217;s security.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So if you&#8217;re ready to give this hack a try, check out our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-custom-login-form-for-improved-site-branding/\">how to create a WordPress custom login form</a>.</p>\n<h3>32. Get More Leads with Mobile-Friendly Signatures</h3>\n<p>All forms created with WPForms are completely responsive and mobile-friendly.</p>\n<p>And, one of the most fantastic hacks to grow your business online is to use Mobile-Friendly Signatures, too.</p>\n<p>Plus, it&#8217;s super easy to add a Signature field to your forms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451613\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/add-Signature-field-in-WPForms-form-builder.jpg\" alt=\"add-Signature-field-in-WPForms-form-builder\" width=\"562\" height=\"527\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/add-Signature-field-in-WPForms-form-builder.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/add-Signature-field-in-WPForms-form-builder-300x281.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>You can ask for signatures for things like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Agreements</li>\n<li>Terms of Service</li>\n<li>Contracts</li>\n<li>Petitions</li>\n<li>Non-Disclosure Agreements</li>\n<li>Any other form you&#8217;d like</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And you can easily add a field for a signature with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/signature-addon/\">Signature Addon</a>.</p>\n<p>Best of all, the Signature Addon is mobile-friendly, meaning you&#8217;ll get more form completions, less form abandonment, and be able to your online business even faster.</p>\n<p>And if you’re looking for a WordPress signature plugin or WordPress contract agreement plugin that&#8217;s mobile-friendly, then you’re definitely going to love this hack.</p>\n<p>So if you&#8217;d like to set this hack up, check out our step by step tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-signature-addon-in-wpforms/\">how to install and user the Signature Addon in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<p>Take a look at our article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/mobile-lead-generation/\">mobile lead generation</a> to learn even more power hacks to grow your business online by optimizing your WordPress forms for mobile.</p>\n<h3>33. Get Paid in Multiple Ways</h3>\n<p>With WPForms, you can use both the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/stripe-addon/\">Stripe Addon</a> and the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/paypal-standard-addon/\">PayPal Standard Addon</a> to collect payments, which can grow your income by giving users choices. Cool, right?</p>\n<p>Well, what&#8217;s even cooler is that you can set up your forms to let your website visitors pick which payment method they want to use, right on your form!</p>\n<p>Meaning, you can make sure your forms only process the payment with the exact payment processor the user selected, and give your visitors more ways to pay you.</p>\n<p>And it&#8217;s all done by using Conditional Logic. Learn more in our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-allow-users-to-choose-a-payment-method-on-your-form/\">how to allow users to choose a payment method on your form</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451656\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/order-form-conditional-payments-1.jpg\" alt=\"order-form-conditional-payments\" width=\"562\" height=\"497\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/order-form-conditional-payments-1.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/order-form-conditional-payments-1-300x265.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Also, if you&#8217;re still on the fence about which payment provider to pick or even considering using both, be sure to check out our in-depth article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/stripe-vs-paypal-which-one-is-better/\">Stripe vs Paypal</a>.</p>\n<h3>34. Set up Recurring Payments to Earn Even More</h3>\n<p>Want a hack that will help skyrocket your website income?</p>\n<p>Conditional Logic also gives you a great trick to increase your website income by choosing between One Time or Recurring Payments.</p>\n<p>One Time payments are awesome for selling a single or multiple products at one point in time.</p>\n<p>But, you can also easily set up your forms to accept Recurring Payments. Meaning more money for you and your small business, time and again.</p>\n<p>Recurring Payments with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/stripe-addon/\">Stripe Addon</a> are available in the following time periods:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Daily</li>\n<li>Weekly</li>\n<li>Monthly</li>\n<li>Quarterly</li>\n<li>Semi-yearly</li>\n<li>Yearly</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And this works great for <a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">membership sites</a>, SaaS products, and anything else you&#8217;d like to bill for repeatedly.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451663\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enable-recurring-payments-example.jpg\" alt=\"enable-recurring-payments-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enable-recurring-payments-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/enable-recurring-payments-example-300x208.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>So to set up recurring payments, read about <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-accept-recurring-payments-on-your-wordpress-form\">how to accept recurring payments on your WordPress forms</a>.</p>\n<h3>35. Use Geolocation to Learn About Your Audience</h3>\n<p>Wanna see where your leads are coming from? Try activating Geolocation as a hack to grow your business online.</p>\n<p>Once you activate Geolocation in your forms, your user’s country, state, and city information will be stored along with their submission.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451669\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/geolocation-in-leads.jpg\" alt=\"geolocation-in-leads\" width=\"562\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/geolocation-in-leads.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/geolocation-in-leads-300x215.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And this hack helps you learn more about your website visitors so you can turn more of them into customers with added insight into where they live.</p>\n<p>So head over to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-geolocation-addon-with-wpforms/\">how to install and use the Geolocation Addon with WPForms</a> to set this up now.</p>\n<h3>36. Brand Email Notifications to Create Connections</h3>\n<p>A simple but super smart hack to make your services stand out is by using branded email notifications.</p>\n<p>With WPForms, you can add your logo or any image you choose to display on your email notifications.</p>\n<p>And this way, when a customer or anyone on your team gets an email notification from your forms, they&#8217;ll see the image you want them to see. You can help build trust and a relationship right inside your email notification.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451670\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/branded-email-notifications.jpg\" alt=\"branded-email-notifications\" width=\"562\" height=\"435\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/branded-email-notifications.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/branded-email-notifications-300x232.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>So set up this clever hack today. Here’s an in-depth tutorial on <a title=\"How to Add Custom Header Image in your WPForms Email Template\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-add-custom-header-image-in-your-wpforms-email-template/\">how to add custom header images in WPForms email template</a>.</p>\n<h3>37. Use NPS Surveys to Learn About Your Visitors</h3>\n<p>This is one of our favorite hacks on our list because it&#8217;s a great way to get to know your customers.</p>\n<p>Net Promoter Score Surveys can give you valuable visual insights into what&#8217;s happening with your business based on customer perception of your brand.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-212972\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/NPS-Calculations.gif\" alt=\"NPS Calculations\" width=\"562\" height=\"403\" /></p>\n<p>And they help you to better gauge customer loyalty and make your business more successful with one simple question: <strong>How likely are you to recommend our company to a friend or colleague?</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451672\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/nps-survey-example.jpg\" alt=\"nps-survey-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/nps-survey-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/nps-survey-example-300x128.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Using Conditional Logic, you can even setup different fields to appear based on different user selections.</p>\n<p>For example, if someone selected a low rating, you could ask them what you could do better in the future. Knowing this helps you make critical business decisions and uncover and work toward any needed improvements.</p>\n<p>If a user selects a 10, you could get details on what they love about your brand so you can make sure to keep doing it:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-256396\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/NPS-Enhanced-Survey-Form-Demo.gif\" alt=\"NPS Enhanced Survey Form Demo\" width=\"576\" height=\"339\" /></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s really simple to get started with this smart hack. To do so, head over to our step by step article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-net-promoter-score-nps-survey-in-wordpress/\">how to create a net promoter score NPS survey in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<h3>38. Create an RSVP Form to Organize Events</h3>\n<p>Are you planning an event? Then you should definitely be using a <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a> RSVP form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451691\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-RSVP-form.jpg\" alt=\"wpforms-RSVP-form\" width=\"562\" height=\"488\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-RSVP-form.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-RSVP-form-300x260.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>This is one of the easiest hacks to use to grow your business online while also finding out who is attending your event and who isn&#8217;t.</p>\n<p>We know your hours of the day are limited. And spending time opening letters, jotting down details, and compiling all the data isn’t all that fun or efficient.</p>\n<p>And not to mention, making the RSVP process easy for your guests makes it easier for them to respond. You’ll get a higher response rate by sharing a link to confirm rather than asking for their replies via snail mail.</p>\n<p>Check out this <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/demo/simple-rsvp-form-demo/\">Simple RSVP Form Demo</a> to see this hack in action.</p>\n<p>Some events you might want to use an RSVP form for include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/demo/birthday-party-invitation-rsvp-form-demo/\">Birthday Parties</a>.</strong> Easily get a headcount of attendees coming to your bash.</li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/demo/wedding-invitation-rsvp-form-demo/\">Weddings</a>.</strong> Gather extra details in your invites like meal preferences.</li>\n<li><strong>Business Events.</strong> Accept registrations and even sell tickets to your event right on your form.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Want to set up and send out an RSVP form right now? Head over to our article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-an-rsvp-form-in-wordpress/\">how to create an RSVP form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<h3>39. Collect More Leads With Offline Forms</h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/offline-forms-addon/\">Offline Forms Addon</a> is our final hack but is also one of the greatest power hacks to grow your business online.</p>\n<p>And that&#8217;s because you&#8217;ll never lose data or leads again just because someone lost their internet connection and gave up on sending you their information.</p>\n<p>You could be the best business out there with a lightning-fast site, but you still can&#8217;t control the quality of your visitor&#8217;s internet connection.</p>\n<p>The Offline Forms Addon allows your users to save their entered data offline. Then, they can submit it when their internet connection is restored.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-451696\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Offline-mode-message-WPForms.jpg\" alt=\"Offline-mode-message-WPForms\" width=\"562\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Offline-mode-message-WPForms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Offline-mode-message-WPForms-300x224.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>This could be super helpful for you to use yourself, too. For example, if you&#8217;re at a trade show collecting leads in person and the event has a spotty Wi-Fi connection.</p>\n<p>We know that the key to getting the most from your forms is to make it as simple and easy as possible for users to submit their info.</p>\n<p>Get this excellent hack up and running by heading over to our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-set-up-the-offline-forms-addon/\">how to install and setup the Offline Forms Addon</a>.</p>\n<h3>Final Thoughts</h3>\n<p>There you have it! Hopefully, this article helped you learn how to grow your business online with tons of new power hacks and the unique features of WPForms.</p>\n<p>Be sure to check out our article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/online-form-statistics-facts/\">unbelievable online form statistics</a> to learn even more about the power of growing your small business with forms on your website.</p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget, if you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/\">39 WPForms Power Hacks To Grow Your Business Online</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:74:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"WPForms vs Typeform: Which Form Builder Is Better?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-vs-typeform/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-vs-typeform/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 24 Apr 2019 12:00:13 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"contact form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"form abandonment\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPForms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"survey form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=435362\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:558:\"<p>Not sure if WPForms vs Typeform is the right form builder for you and your website? WPForms and Typeform are both popular tools to add forms and surveys to WordPress sites, but they&#8217;re absolutely not the same. Actually, there are some huge differences between them, and picking the right one could lead to massive growth. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-vs-typeform/\">WPForms vs Typeform: Which Form Builder Is Better?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19495:\"<p>Not sure if WPForms vs Typeform is the right form builder for you and your website?</p>\n<p>WPForms and Typeform are both popular tools to add forms and surveys to WordPress sites, but they&#8217;re absolutely not the same. Actually, there are some huge differences between them, and picking the right one could lead to massive growth.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll compare WPForms vs Typeform so you can decide which one will work best for your needs.</p>\n<h3>Which Form Builder Is Better?</h3>\n<p>We&#8217;ve taken a close look at the most important factors for you to decide which form builder is right for your business. Here&#8217;s a table of contents for easy navigation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#overview\"><strong>Overview</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#ease\"><strong>Ease of Use</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#conversationalforms\"><strong>Conversational Forms</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#customersupport\"><strong>Customer Support</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#integrations\"><strong>Integrations</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pricing\"><strong>Pricing</strong></a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#bottomline\"><strong>Bottom Line: WPForms vs Typeform</strong></a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>So, let&#8217;s get started and take a closer look at our WPForms vs Typeform comparison:</p>\n<h3 id=\"overview\">Overview</h3>\n<p>WPForms and Typeform are both form builders that let you add forms to your site. But, there are some major differences between WPForms vs Typeform and how they work.</p>\n<p><strong>WPForms</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-435534\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-does-wpforms-work.jpg\" alt=\"how-does-wpforms-work\" width=\"562\" height=\"507\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-does-wpforms-work.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-does-wpforms-work-300x271.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>WPForms is the most beginner-friendly form builder in the market. It&#8217;s a WordPress plugin that lets you create forms easily with a drag and drop builder. Everything happens directly on your website. No coding needed!</p>\n<p>With WPForms, you can create surveys, polls, contact forms, RSVPs, order forms, and much more.</p>\n<p>WPForms has 100+ pre-built templates for your forms to meet your exact needs, or you can start one from scratch. You can use WPForms to build simple forms, more complex forms, and even beautiful Conversational Forms.</p>\n<p><strong>Typeform</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-435532\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/what-is-typeform.jpg\" alt=\"what-is-typeform\" width=\"562\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/what-is-typeform.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/what-is-typeform-300x207.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Typeform is a web-based form builder. To clarify, it&#8217;s not a WordPress plugin.</p>\n<p>In other words, it&#8217;s a standalone tool that lets you build forms on their website. You need to login to their site to create your forms. Then, must copy/paste the code for the form into your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>And, if you&#8217;re <strong>not</strong> using WordPress, you can <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/how-to-install-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">learn how to easily setup a WordPress site here</a>.</p>\n<p>Typeform is somewhat beginner-friendly.</p>\n<p>Above all, it focuses on making slick-looking surveys that are fun and conversational for your audience. With Typeform, you can focus on gathering data by asking your customers questions in a very modern way.</p>\n<p>And besides surveys, you can also use Typeform to build things like contact forms, quizzes, shopping carts, and feedback forms. Their form builder lets you chose from some good-looking templates to help you start creating a form quickly.</p>\n<p>However, Typeform lacks a lot of the features that WPForms offers. Let&#8217;s take a deeper look.</p>\n<h3 id=\"ease\">Ease of Use</h3>\n<p>Creating a form on your website should be easy. So, the process needs to be beginner-friendly. And you shouldn&#8217;t have to use any code. Let&#8217;s take a peek at how WPForms vs Typeform match up with ease of use.</p>\n<p><strong>WPForms</strong></p>\n<p>Beginners love WPForms for good reason. One reason is because it&#8217;s super user-friendly. You can easily make forms in minutes by using a drag and drop builder, right in WordPress. Even gorgeous Conversational Forms are simple to create with WPForms.</p>\n<p>One of the places where WPForms really shines is with how simple it is to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">add your form to your WordPress website</a>.</p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t need to use any code because the WPForms plugin handles this all for you. And you can choose to add your forms to pages, posts, sidebars, footers, or any other widget areas on your site.</p>\n<p>Using the WPForms <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-templates-pack-addon/\">Form Templates Pack Addon,</a> you get access to 100+ pre-built templates for a variety of needs. These templates are lifesavers because they save you tons of time building your forms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436509\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-tempates.jpg\" alt=\"wpforms-tempates\" width=\"562\" height=\"476\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-tempates.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-tempates-300x254.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And you can easily add fields by dragging them from the left side to the right side. Likewise, deleting fields is as simple as 1 click.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436554\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/edit-wpforms-surveys.jpg\" alt=\"edit-wpforms-surveys\" width=\"562\" height=\"358\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/edit-wpforms-surveys.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/edit-wpforms-surveys-300x191.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>In addition, customizing your Conversational Forms is very simple with WPForms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436546\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-survey-builder.jpg\" alt=\"wpforms-survey-builder\" width=\"562\" height=\"562\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-survey-builder.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-survey-builder-150x150.jpg 150w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-survey-builder-300x300.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-survey-builder-100x100.jpg 100w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a class=\"btn btn-block\" style=\"background-color: #e2772f !important; color: #fff !important; padding: 20px 25px !important; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px !important; -moz-border-radius: 4px !important; -webkit-border-radius: 4px !important; font-weight: bold;\" title=\"Click Here to See Conversational Forms in Action\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/conversational-forms-demo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click Here to See Conversational Forms in Action</a></p>\n<p><strong>Typeform</strong></p>\n<p>Using Typeform might be a little difficult for some beginners.</p>\n<p>So, although it&#8217;s fairly easy to create a pretty survey form with Typeform, inserting the form into your site can be hard.</p>\n<p>For instance, when you&#8217;re ready to add the form you&#8217;ve built to your website, you need to go to your site&#8217;s HTML text editor. Here, you&#8217;ll inset the HTML code for your Typeform form exactly where you want it to show up on your website. This can be a difficult task for beginners.</p>\n<p>The 60+ templates Typeform provides are designed for things like surveys, feedback, questionnaires, and more.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436503\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-template.jpg\" alt=\"typeform-template\" width=\"562\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-template.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-template-300x214.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Beginners might also feel a little intimated by the advanced way you customize your forms with Typeform.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436517\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-survey-builder.jpg\" alt=\"typeform-survey-builder\" width=\"562\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-survey-builder.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-survey-builder-300x217.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"conversationalforms\">Conversational Forms</h3>\n<p>Conversational forms are beautiful and interactive forms. They act as a conversation between you and your visitors. Both WPForms and Typeform offer Conversational Forms. Let&#8217;s take a closer look.</p>\n<p><strong>WPForms</strong></p>\n<p>Conversational forms are a great feature on top of tons of other options in WPForms. They look great and are so engaging.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-435433\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/interactive-conversational-forms-example.gif\" alt=\"interactive-conversational-forms-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"405\" /></p>\n<p>Most importantly, these interactive forms boost form completion and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-combat-order-form-abandonment-and-increase-your-sales/\">decrease form abandonment</a>.</p>\n<p>And WPForms lets you connect your Conversational Forms to all of the top email marketing services.</p>\n<p>So, although Typeform also has beautiful full-page Conversational Forms, WPForms adds a ton of unique features to their forms like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Signature Addon. </strong>Lets users sign your form electronically.</li>\n<li><strong>Geolocation Data. </strong>See where your users are on a map.</li>\n<li><strong>User Registration. </strong>Let users register for things like your forums, eCommerce, and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-membership-plugins-compared/\">membership sites</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Custom Captcha. </strong>Use custom or math questions to make sure your user is human.</li>\n<li><strong>Form Abandonment Addon. </strong>Get more leads by capturing partial entries.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Typeform</strong></p>\n<p>Typeform focuses heavily on Conversational Forms. They have some hip looking templates that help you build these interactive forms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436632\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-full-page-conversational-forms.jpg\" alt=\"typeform-full-page-conversational-forms\" width=\"562\" height=\"316\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-full-page-conversational-forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-full-page-conversational-forms-300x169.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>It uses the logic jump feature to ask different questions based on someone&#8217;s answer to the last question.</p>\n<p>You can build surveys and questionnaires, quizzes, polls, and more. All as Conversational Forms.</p>\n<h3 id=\"customersupport\">Customer Support</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s super important to have fast and helpful customer service when you have a question or need help with your forms.</p>\n<p>You should be able to access and successfully complete simple tasks by following easy and clear instructions in your form builder&#8217;s documentation hub. These docs need to be easily understood by everyone, even beginners.</p>\n<p>So, let&#8217;s check out how WPForms vs Typeform compare in this area.</p>\n<p><strong>WPForms</strong></p>\n<p>The support at WPForms is excellent. In fact, it&#8217;s one of the best things about WPForms.</p>\n<p>For example, you can open your own support ticket, and the team usually responds to requests within 24 hours on weekdays. It doesn&#8217;t matter which level of plan you use have WPForms, because you get direct help from a real person even with the WPForms basic plan.</p>\n<p>Support staff is friendly, helpful, and they genuinely care about doing the right thing for their customers.</p>\n<p>You can also visit their <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/\">Documentation center</a> and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/blog/\">blog</a> for step by step tutorials.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-436638 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-help-documentation.jpg\" alt=\"wpforms-help-documentation\" width=\"562\" height=\"308\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-help-documentation.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforms-help-documentation-300x164.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Typeform</strong></p>\n<p>Typeform has a mix of different ways to get help.</p>\n<p>They have a blog and use a Help Center with documentation.</p>\n<p>However, getting support on Typeform is limited. The Basic free plan restricts you to just ten questions per form.</p>\n<p>So, you need to be on at least a Pro or Pro+ premium plan to get direct support from the customer success team.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-436656\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-help-docs.jpg\" alt=\"typeform-help-docs\" width=\"562\" height=\"264\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-help-docs.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/typeform-help-docs-300x141.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"integrations\">Integrations</h3>\n<p>Your online form builder should also have lots of integrations to help you manage all kinds of forms.</p>\n<p>They should connect with tools like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>PayPal</li>\n<li>Stripe</li>\n<li>Zapier</li>\n<li><a title=\"Drip\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Constant Contact\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a></li>\n<li>And More</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Of course, WPForms vs Typeform both have tons of integrations with fantastic tools including those listed above and others.</p>\n<h3 id=\"pricing\">Pricing</h3>\n<p>Not everyone can afford a ton of money on form builders. So, the one you buy should have an inclusive pricing plan. Meaning, all of their services and features are affordable to use for everyone.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s check out how the costs of WPForms and Typeform add up.</p>\n<p><strong>WPForms</strong></p>\n<p>WPForms has 4 different pricing plans: Basic, Plus, Pro, and Elite. These plans start at $39.50 to $299.50 per year.</p>\n<p>This pricing is great for small businesses and website owners looking for a simple tool with powerful features. As a result, you don&#8217;t have hire an expensive developer and can stay within your budget.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-435525\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-much-does-wpforms-cost.jpg\" alt=\"how-much-does-wpforms-cost\" width=\"562\" height=\"649\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-much-does-wpforms-cost.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-much-does-wpforms-cost-260x300.jpg 260w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>To access features like Conversational Forms and payment integration, you&#8217;ll want to pick the Pro plan. This is the most popular WPForms plan.</p>\n<p>Also, WPForms has a really great refund policy. If you buy a WPForms plan and change your mind for any reason in the next 14 days, they will refund 100% of your money.</p>\n<p><strong>Typeform</strong></p>\n<p>Typeform has 3 different pricing plans to pick from: Basic (free), Pro, and Pro+. Per year, Pro costs $360 and Pro+ costs $700.</p>\n<p>But, the pricing can be expensive for beginner website owners. Especially if you&#8217;re looking to create more than just Conversational Forms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-435524\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-much-does-typeform-cost.jpg\" alt=\"how-much-does-typeform-cost\" width=\"562\" height=\"419\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-much-does-typeform-cost.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-much-does-typeform-cost-300x224.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>The Basic (free) plan has very little features and integrations.</p>\n<p>So, it&#8217;s best for trial runs because it only allows you to collect 100 responses to your form. Also, it doesn&#8217;t let you use logic jump, upload files, or take payments.</p>\n<p>To get unlimited answers to your forms, you&#8217;ll need to go with The Pro and Pro+ plans with Typeform.</p>\n<h3 id=\"bottomline\">Bottom Line: WPForms vs Typeform</h3>\n<p>So, which is better? WPForms vs Typeform?</p>\n<p>In short, if you&#8217;re still trying to decide which form builder is the right one for you, your best option is <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n<p>Although Typeform has a trendy looking website, WPForms is the most beloved and easy form builder plugin out there for a reason. And WPForms offers nearly everything Typeform does and more.</p>\n<p>In addition:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>WPForms comes with a 100% no-risk money back guarantee.</strong> The support team will help you get your refund without question.</li>\n<li><strong>WPForms is more affordable</strong>. The most expensive WPForms plan is $299.50 a year. On the other hand, with Typeform, you&#8217;ll spend $700+ a year for a service that lets you create Conversational Forms only. Conversational Forms are an added feature to WPForms, which is one of the reasons why it&#8217;s such a better value.</li>\n<li><strong>WPForms is a WordPress plugin. </strong>The form builder was created with WordPress uses in mind, so it&#8217;s more suitable if you&#8217;re using WordPress.</li>\n<li><strong>WPForms is easier. </strong>No code required. WPForms is super user-friendly and is perfect for beginners.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! You now know a lot more about both WPForms and Typeform and can make an educated decision on which is better and what will work best for your website.</p>\n<p>If you need some ideas to start using your forms, check out this article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-wpbeginner-uses-wpforms-to-grow-their-business/\">how to use WPForms to grow your business.</a></p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget, if you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-vs-typeform/\">WPForms vs Typeform: Which Form Builder Is Better?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-vs-typeform/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"WPForms + StudioPress: Beautiful WordPress Websites Made Easy\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-studiopress-beautiful-wordpress-websites-made-easy/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-studiopress-beautiful-wordpress-websites-made-easy/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 23 Apr 2019 14:08:59 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Announcement\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"wordpress hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"managed hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"wordpress themes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"studiopress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=454226\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:622:\"<p>Creating your own website from scratch can be a huge challenge, especially if you&#8217;re not a coder. That&#8217;s why it&#8217;s been our goal from the beginning to make it easy for anyone to build smart forms without needing a designer or developer. And that&#8217;s why today, we&#8217;re excited to announce our new partnership with WP [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-studiopress-beautiful-wordpress-websites-made-easy/\">WPForms + StudioPress: Beautiful WordPress Websites Made Easy</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4077:\"<p>Creating your own website from scratch can be a huge challenge, especially if you&#8217;re not a coder. That&#8217;s why it&#8217;s been our goal from the beginning to make it easy for anyone to build smart forms without needing a designer or developer.</p>\n<p>And that&#8217;s why today, we&#8217;re excited to announce our new partnership with WP Engine&#8217;s StudioPress.</p>\n<p><a  title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" >WP Engine</a> is a managed WordPress hosting provider, with StudioPress Themes offered as part of their world-class hosting platform.</p>\n<p>Now every step of creating your website &#8211; from choosing the best web host and WordPress theme, to creating web forms &#8211; is easier than ever.</p>\n<h3>StudioPress and the Genesis Framework</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/studiopress.jpg\" alt=\"studiopress\" width=\"560\" height=\"293\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-454240\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/studiopress.jpg 560w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/studiopress-300x157.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /><br />\nStudioPress themes make it easy to create beautiful, fast, and <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ultimate-seo-guide/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">SEO-friendly websites</a> in no time.</p>\n<p>StudioPress is the creator of the Genesis <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/what-is-a-theme-framework/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">theme framework</a>. With the Genesis framework, you can choose from dozens of uniquely designed themes that are fast, secure, and well-coded.</p>\n<p>Now StudioPress is partnering with WPForms so that you can <strong>automatically install WPForms along with your theme in just one click</strong>. This feature is included in their latest themes including Revolution Pro‚ Monochrome Pro, and the Genesis Sample theme which is a great base for developers to code their own themes.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/themes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"395\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-454241\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/themes.jpg 560w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/themes-300x212.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<h3>Get StudioPress Themes Free With WP Engine</h3>\n<p>Now you can get access to StudioPress themes for free when you get managed WordPress hosting from <a  title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" >WP Engine</a>.</p>\n<p>WP Engine offers hassle-free managed WordPress hosting that&#8217;s incredibly fast. They’re known for their reliability and WordPress Expert support, which gets rave reviews from their customers. They offer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>automatic security updates</li>\n<li>daily backups with one-click restore points</li>\n<li>automatic caching for <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-performance-speed/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">fast loading sites</a></li>\n<li>top-tier <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress security</a></li>\n<li>one-click staging area</li>\n<li>&#8230;and more</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you’re busy running a business and don’t want to deal with the technical side of running your blog, then <a  title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" >WP Engine</a> is the solution for you.</p>\n<p>We’re excited to work with WP Engine to bring a better form-building experience to more businesses worldwide.</p>\n<p>Not using WPForms yet? <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">Click here to unlock the power of WPForms today</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-studiopress-beautiful-wordpress-websites-made-easy/\">WPForms + StudioPress: Beautiful WordPress Websites Made Easy</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-studiopress-beautiful-wordpress-websites-made-easy/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"7 Best Managed WordPress Hosting for 2019 (Compared)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wpforms.com/best-managed-wordpress-hosting/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wpforms.com/best-managed-wordpress-hosting/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 22 Apr 2019 12:00:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"web hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"bluehost\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"wordpress hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"managed hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=437442\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:573:\"<p>Are you looking for a managed hosting provider for your WordPress website? A managed WordPress host takes care of all the technical stuff of your site and allows you to concentrate on your business. In the article, we&#8217;ll compare the best managed WordPress hosting companies and help you to choose the right service for your [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-managed-wordpress-hosting/\">7 Best Managed WordPress Hosting for 2019 (Compared)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Sandipan Mukherjee\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19647:\"<p>Are you looking for a managed hosting provider for your WordPress website? A managed WordPress host takes care of all the technical stuff of your site and allows you to concentrate on your business.</p>\n<p>In the article, we&#8217;ll compare the best managed WordPress hosting companies and help you to choose the right service for your website.</p>\n<h3>What is Managed WordPress Hosting?</h3>\n<p>A managed WordPress hosting is a service that provides the best infrastructure for your WordPress website and helps you with the essential tasks including daily backups and security checks.</p>\n<p>And unlike a shared hosting service, it assists you to optimize your site for speed.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-441178\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/speed-up-using-managed-wordpress-hosting.png\" alt=\"speed up using managed WordPress hosting\" width=\"562\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/speed-up-using-managed-wordpress-hosting.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/speed-up-using-managed-wordpress-hosting-300x133.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at the advantages of using managed WordPress hosting:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fast and secure compared to shared hosting services.</li>\n<li>Daily automatic backup of your website and database.</li>\n<li>Expert support team to help you to solve your WordPress related problems.</li>\n<li>Takes care of the core WordPress and plugin updates.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here are some of the cons of managed WordPress hosting:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Limitations on using specific plugins that may slow down your website.</li>\n<li>It&#8217;s expensive as compared to shared web hosts.</li>\n<li>You can host WordPress based websites only, not even simple HTML sites.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Things to Look For in a Managed WordPress Host</h3>\n<p>First of all, you should understand one thing: we don&#8217;t recommend a managed hosting service provider to everyone.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re just starting out, you can easily use a regular or shared hosting service like <a title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Bluehost</a>. They also provide free domain and professional email with their service.</p>\n<p>However, if you&#8217;ve got a high traffic website or you&#8217;re not confident with the technical aspects of running a WordPress site, then you should use managed WordPress hosting service.</p>\n<p>But with so many hosting providers out there, how to decide which managed hosting company is suitable for your needs?</p>\n<p>Here are the essential factors to look for before choosing a managed host:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fast, reliable, and secure service.</li>\n<li>Daily backups of your website.</li>\n<li>Free SSL (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/ssl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Secure Sockets Layer</a>) and CDN (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/best-wordpress-cdn-services/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Content Delivery Network</a>).</li>\n<li>Expert customer support team.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Best Managed WordPress Hosting in 2019</h3>\n<p>By now, you should have made up your mind that you need to buy or migrate to a managed WordPress hosting for your website.</p>\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s take a look at the best managed WordPress hosting in 2019.</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Our sister site <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPBeginner</a> recently conducted speed tests on some of the hosting service providers listed here. And we&#8217;ll be using those results to give you a better idea about each of them.</p>\n<h3>1. <a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WP Engine</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439651\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpengine-hosting.png\" alt=\"WP Engine Hosting\" width=\"562\" height=\"306\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpengine-hosting.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpengine-hosting-300x163.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WP Engine is a fast and reliable managed WordPress hosting provider. It&#8217;s one of the most popular managed hosts in the market.</p>\n<p>WP Engine comes with some fantastic features like daily automated backups, Let&#8217;s Encrypt SSL certificates, disaster recovery system, and handles core WordPress updates.</p>\n<p>It also offers the Genesis framework and 35+ StudioPress themes with every plan. Isn&#8217;t that great?</p>\n<p>Not only that, but they also provide free CDN to all their customers. This will help your website to be faster as compared to your competitors.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at the speed test result of WP Engine:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-441012\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpengine-speed-test.png\" alt=\"WP Engine Speed Test\" width=\"562\" height=\"244\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpengine-speed-test.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpengine-speed-test-300x130.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>WP Engine is well known for providing excellent customer support. They&#8217;ve got a team of trained WordPress experts who are ready to help you at any time of the day.</p>\n<p>The startup plan of WP Engine starts at $35 per month. It allows you to host just one website with a traffic limit of 25,000 per month. And you can always upgrade to a higher plan to host more sites.</p>\n<p>Planning to migrate your site to WP Engine but scared of the technical stuff involved? Don&#8217;t worry! Their expert team will handle the migration process for you at no additional cost.</p>\n<h3>2. <a title=\"Siteground\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SiteGround</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Siteground\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439649\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/siteground-managed-hosting.png\" alt=\"SiteGround Managed Hosting\" width=\"562\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/siteground-managed-hosting.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/siteground-managed-hosting-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a WP Engine alternative, then you can certainly use SiteGround managed hosting. And the best part is they&#8217;re one of the officially recommended hosting providers by WordPress.org.</p>\n<p>Though SiteGround is a popular shared hosting provider, they also offer powerful managed hosting service. They use the latest technologies to make sure your <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wordpress-com-vs-wordpress-org-pros-and-cons-compared/\">WordPress website</a> is fast and suffers zero downtime.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at some of the features of SiteGround:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Free SSL certificates by Let&#8217;s Encrypt.</li>\n<li>Create unlimited professional email accounts.</li>\n<li>Free Cloudflare CDN to make your site faster.</li>\n<li>One-click staging tool to create a copy of your website, do necessary changes to it, and then make it live.</li>\n<li>Free site migration service.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Like most hosting providers on our list, SiteGround takes daily backups to make sure your data is always safe. They keep up to 30 backup copies which can be restored quickly. You can even manually backup your site with a single click.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the speed test result of SiteGround:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-441011\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/speed-test-siteground.jpg\" alt=\"SiteGround Speed Test\" width=\"562\" height=\"224\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/speed-test-siteground.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/speed-test-siteground-300x120.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>You can purchase the basic or startup plan of SiteGround at $3.95 per month. However, you&#8217;ll be allowed to host just one website and free site migration is not included with this plan.</p>\n<p>We would instead recommend you to use the GrowBig plan which is priced at $5.95 per month to avail all the features.</p>\n<h3>3. <a title=\"Bluehost Optimized\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost-optimized/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Bluehost Optimized</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Bluehost Optimized\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost-optimized/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439643\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-optimized-hosting-for-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Bluehost Optimized Hosting for WordPress\" width=\"562\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-optimized-hosting-for-wordpress.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-optimized-hosting-for-wordpress-300x139.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Bluehost is a popular shared hosting service and just like SiteGround, it&#8217;s also recommended by WordPress.org.</p>\n<p>However, we&#8217;ll not be talking about their shared hosting service here; instead, we&#8217;ll take a look at their WordPress Optimized service called Bluehost Optimized.</p>\n<p>Before talking about the features of Bluehost Optimized, let&#8217;s take a look at the speed test results:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-441008\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-speed-test.jpg\" alt=\"Bluehost Speed Test\" width=\"562\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-speed-test.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-speed-test-300x114.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Bluehost Optimized service uses VPS technologies and thus makes sure <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-security/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">your site is secure</a> and extremely fast.</p>\n<p>They offer a free domain with all their plans. Also, you&#8217;ll get free CDN, daily backups, SSL, and business email service. And you can manage everything from their enhanced cPanel.</p>\n<p>The basic plan of Bluehost Optimized is called <strong>wp standard</strong> and will cost you $19.99 per month. This plan allows you to receive up to 100 million visits per month.</p>\n<h3>4. <a title=\"DreamPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/dreampress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">DreamPress by DreamHost</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"DreamPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/dreampress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439644\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dreampress-by-dreamhost.png\" alt=\"DreamPress by DreamHost\" width=\"562\" height=\"256\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dreampress-by-dreamhost.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dreampress-by-dreamhost-300x137.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>DreamHost is one of the oldest hosting companies in the market and is known for its reliable service. They&#8217;re also officially recommended by WordPress.org.</p>\n<p>DreamHost offers managed WordPress hosting service, known as DreamPress. Here are some of the amazing features provided by DreamPress:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Built-in <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-install-and-setup-w3-total-cache-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">caching system</a>.</li>\n<li>Automatic backups with one-click restore option.</li>\n<li>Free migration service with every DreamPress plan.</li>\n<li>Pre-installed Let&#8217;s Encrypt SSL certificates.</li>\n<li>24/7 expert support for solving your problems.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now let&#8217;s check out the speed test results of DreamHost:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-441009\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dreamhost-speed-test.png\" alt=\"DreamHost Speed Test\" width=\"562\" height=\"232\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dreamhost-speed-test.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dreamhost-speed-test-300x124.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see, the test site loaded in less than a second which is quite impressive.</p>\n<p>Anyways, along with all the fantastic features, DreamHost also provides a free domain with privacy protection to all its customers.</p>\n<p>The pricing of DreamPress hosting starts from $16.95 per month. They also offer a money-back guarantee with all their plans.</p>\n<h3>5. <a title=\"HostGator Cloud\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hostgator-cloud/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">HostGator Cloud</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"HostGator Cloud\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hostgator-cloud/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439645\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hostgator-cloud-hosting.png\" alt=\"HostGator Cloud Hosting\" width=\"562\" height=\"255\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hostgator-cloud-hosting.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/hostgator-cloud-hosting-300x136.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>HostGator is a well-known shared hosting service among bloggers and small businesses.</p>\n<p>One of the services of Hostgator for high traffic sites is Hostgator Cloud. It&#8217;s a cloud hosting service that loads your website 2 times faster than your normal shared host.</p>\n<p>Some of the features of HostGator Cloud are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Integrated caching to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-performance-speed/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">speed up your site</a>.</li>\n<li>Easy to understand dashboard to keep track of everything.</li>\n<li>Offers cPanel to manage things like email, domains, and more.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Unlike most hosting providers, Hostgator Cloud doesn&#8217;t provide website backup and restore feature. However, you can purchase CodeGuard addon to keep your website data safe.</p>\n<p>Finally, let&#8217;s talk about the pricing plans of Hostgator Cloud. The Hatchling Cloud plan can be purchased at $4.95 per month and allows you to host only one domain. However, their Baby and Business plans do not have any such restrictions.</p>\n<h3>6. <a title=\"LiquidWeb\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/liquidweb/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Liquid Web</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"LiquidWeb\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/liquidweb/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439646\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/liquid-web-hosting.png\" alt=\"Liquid Web Hosting\" width=\"562\" height=\"270\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/liquid-web-hosting.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/liquid-web-hosting-300x144.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Liquid Web is a fully managed web hosting company. They provide complete service for your WordPress websites.</p>\n<p>Plus, they&#8217;re one of the few companies to offer managed WooCommerce hosting service for your online stores.</p>\n<p>Liquid Web uses the latest technologies including PHP7 and NGINX web servers. Also, each of their hosting plans comes bundled with an image optimization plugin to help you to improve the speed of your WordPress website.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the speed test result of Liquid Web:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-441010\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/liquidweb-speed-test.png\" alt=\"Liquid Web Speed Test\" width=\"562\" height=\"242\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/liquidweb-speed-test.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/liquidweb-speed-test-300x129.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Liquid Web offers tons of useful features like automatic daily backups, staging site, SSL certificate, 24/7 support, and free migration service.</p>\n<p>You can host a single website with them for $29 per month. And to host more sites, you&#8217;ve to upgrade to a higher plan.</p>\n<h3>7. <a title=\"Pagely\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/pagely/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Pagely</a></h3>\n<p><a title=\"Pagely\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/pagely/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-439647\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pagely-hosting.png\" alt=\"Pagely Hosting\" width=\"562\" height=\"243\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pagely-hosting.png 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pagely-hosting-300x130.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Pagely is a reliable managed hosting company. They&#8217;re the one who came up with the concept of managed WordPress hosting.</p>\n<p>Pagely is powered by Amazon Web Services and uses modern technologies to host your website. So you can expect your WordPress site to have unbeatable performance.</p>\n<p>They&#8217;ll handle every technical aspect for you including the core WordPress updates, plugin updates, security, and speed optimization. Plus, you don&#8217;t have to worry about taking backups as your entire site and database will be automatically backed up on a daily basis.</p>\n<p>Pagely offers some developer tools like SSH, GIT, WP CLI, and REST API for their advanced users. However, most of them are available on their higher tier packages only.</p>\n<p>Last but not least, let&#8217;s talk about the pricing of this managed host. Well, compared to other hosts, Pagely is the most expensive service provider on our list. And the pricing of their basic plan starts from $199 per month.</p>\n<h3>Final Thoughts</h3>\n<p>We compared the features of the 7 most popular managed web hosts in this article. And we can conclude that <a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WPEngine</a> is the best managed WordPress hosting you can use for your website.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a more affordable alternative, then you can go with <a title=\"Siteground\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SiteGround hosting</a>. It&#8217;s another web host that we can highly recommend.</p>\n<p>Anyways, we hope this article helped you to choose a managed web hosting service provider for your WordPress website.</p>\n<p>If you want to know how many people are visiting your website, then check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-track-site-visitors-coming-to-your-wordpress-website/\">how to track site visitors coming to your WordPress site</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, please follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> to get more updates from our blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-managed-wordpress-hosting/\">7 Best Managed WordPress Hosting for 2019 (Compared)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://wpforms.com/best-managed-wordpress-hosting/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"Why You Should Start Building an Email List Right Away in 2019\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://wpforms.com/why-you-should-start-building-an-email-list/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://wpforms.com/why-you-should-start-building-an-email-list/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 18 Apr 2019 12:00:45 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"newsletter\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"email opt-in\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"lead generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"email marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"email list\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=433295\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:596:\"<p>Are you putting off building an email list on your website and need some motivation? The benefits of building an email list are too great to ignore. An email list can have a mind-blowing impact on your website&#8217;s traffic and revenue. Don&#8217;t wait. In this article, we&#8217;ll share the top reasons why 2019 is the year [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/why-you-should-start-building-an-email-list/\">Why You Should Start Building an Email List Right Away in 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17214:\"<p>Are you putting off building an email list on your website and need some motivation? The benefits of building an email list are too great to ignore. An email list can have a mind-blowing impact on your website&#8217;s traffic and revenue. Don&#8217;t wait.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll share the top reasons why 2019 is the year you should start building an email list right away.</p>\n<h3>What Exactly Is an Email List?</h3>\n<p>An email list is simply a list of emails that your website has collected. This mailing list is used to send out emails.</p>\n<p>In other words, you can use your email list to send out new blog posts, business announcements, and to sell your products or services.</p>\n<h3>Should You Buy an Email List?</h3>\n<p>It may seem tempting, but buying an email list is never a good idea.</p>\n<p>People will probably mark your email as spam if they didn&#8217;t sign up for your list. Plus, it&#8217;s not always likely they&#8217;re interested in your products if they&#8217;ve never been to your website.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s not only legal, but also ethical to <strong>only</strong> send emails to people who actually agreed to get emails from you.</p>\n<p>In the end, you rarely get what you pay for when you buy an email list.</p>\n<h3>Benefits of Building an Email List</h3>\n<p>So, a lot of business owners and bloggers who are just starting out don&#8217;t realize how important an email list actually is.</p>\n<p>The power of email lists is in the numbers. According to the Direct Marketing Association, email marketing sees a 4300% average return on investment (ROI) for businesses in the US.</p>\n<p>To get started creating a simple form and email list right away, read our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">how to create a simple contact form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>Here are some other strong reasons why building an email list is so important:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You&#8217;ll Easily Get Messages to Customers</li>\n<li>Get Visitors to Return</li>\n<li>Email Is Personal</li>\n<li>Huge Companies Love Email Lists</li>\n<li>You Own Your Email List</li>\n<li>You&#8217;ll Make More Money</li>\n<li>Email Builds Trust</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a closer look into each of these benefits of building an email list.</p>\n<p><strong>1. You&#8217;ll Easily Get Messages to Customers</strong></p>\n<p>According to Radicati Group, there are over 3.6 billion email users. That&#8217;s more than half of the planet. By 2022, that number will reach 4.2 billion!</p>\n<p>In addition, studies show at least 91% of consumers check their email at least once a day. You can go days without checking your social media. These numbers are part of why building an email list is a no-brainer for smart businesses.</p>\n<p>When you send an email, your words are delivered directly to someone&#8217;s inbox.</p>\n<p>However, due to the nature of social media, your customer is much more likely to miss your update in their feed.</p>\n<p>This shows why email lists are important and much more effective at getting your message in front of your customer than social media.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Get Visitors to Return</strong></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s a scary but true fact:</p>\n<p>More than 70% of people leaving your website <strong>never</strong> return. For proof, just take a look at your Google Analytics and check out the percentage of new vs returning visitors.</p>\n<p>And your visitors are valuable. Out of all the websites in the world, they&#8217;ve ended up on yours.</p>\n<p>What you don&#8217;t want is miss the chance to turn a casual web surfer into an avid fan who visits your site all the time.</p>\n<p>People are much more likely to come back to your website when they see an email in their inbox from you. Invite them back with another great post, a well-written announcement, or a special sale.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Email Is Personal</strong></p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t you feel more interested in an email that starts by using your name?</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-435355\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/personalized-email-list-example.jpg\" alt=\"personalized-email-list-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/personalized-email-list-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/personalized-email-list-example-300x274.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Consumers love this.</p>\n<p>Personalization helps your email marketing go from average to great. Don&#8217;t lose revenue by ignoring personalization. Check out our sister site&#8217;s article with <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ecommerce-personalization-examples/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">eCommerce personalization examples</a> to help lift your sales.</p>\n<p>Of course, you can personalize your messages to your email list with email marketing services like <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a>.</p>\n<p>In addition, email is very direct. Every person on your list gets an email the same way they get a piece of mail. It&#8217;s so different from seeing a message in a newsfeed as they scroll by.</p>\n<p>Also, just the act of receiving an email is personal. For example, people get emails from your business in the very same inbox they get emails from their parents.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Huge Companies Love Email Lists</strong></p>\n<p>Take a lesson from the digital marketing playbook of the biggest brands in the world. They spend tons of money on campaigns just to get people to sign up for their email list.</p>\n<p>For example, just think about the last website you visited to buy things like clothes, shoes or jewelry. Chances are, they asked for your email.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-434558\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/email-list-lead-magnet-example.jpg\" alt=\"email-list-lead-magnet-example\" width=\"562\" height=\"271\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/email-list-lead-magnet-example.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/email-list-lead-magnet-example-300x145.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>These big brands are smart to use social media to build an email list on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and others. They focus so much energy on building their email lists because they&#8217;ve seen amazing results.</p>\n<p>They know that email lists are super valuable and building an email list helps boost sales. Big name companies understand that email lists are fantastic long-term investments that have high returns for low costs.</p>\n<p>Even the social media companies themselves know how important it is to send messages to their email lists:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-434662\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/why-to-build-an-email-list.jpg\" alt=\"why-to-build-an-email-list\" width=\"562\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/why-to-build-an-email-list.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/why-to-build-an-email-list-300x135.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>5. You Own Your Email List</strong></p>\n<p>Except for your website, your email list is the only thing you have control over when it comes to your online business.</p>\n<p>For instance, you may have thousands of followers on Facebook, Twitter, or LinkedIn, but those followers actually belong to those companies.</p>\n<p>However, one of the biggest benefits of building an email list is that your list is <strong>all yours</strong>.</p>\n<p>Of course, you can&#8217;t control when a social media platform changes its policies. Those changes can influence your campaigns. Getting complete control over your subscriber list and focusing on building your email list is a smart business move.</p>\n<p><strong>6. You&#8217;ll Make More Money</strong></p>\n<p>Imagine that each one of your website visitors is a lead. Doesn&#8217;t it make sense to ask for their info so you can follow-up with them?</p>\n<p>You already know they&#8217;re interested in your niche since they&#8217;re on your site.</p>\n<p>Because of this, subscribers are much more likely to become buyers. Since these people joined your email list from your site, you know they&#8217;re already very interested in what you&#8217;re offering.</p>\n<p>Your subscribers put in the work to hear from you!</p>\n<p>Also, since the average ROI on email marketing is 4300%, it ends up being incredibly inexpensive.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Email Builds Trust</strong></p>\n<p>Sending emails to your customer builds trust between you and them.</p>\n<p>When people read an email from you, they do it in the privacy of their inbox. It&#8217;s not a message displayed publicly on a billboard or a social media timeline.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s a more intimate way to communicate.</p>\n<p>Because email lists let customers feel like they&#8217;re part of a private conversation, they can ask you questions confidently by replying to your message. This helps build trust and a connection.</p>\n<h3>How Do I Grow My Email List?</h3>\n<p>There are tons of ways to grow your email list. Some of the most popular ways include:</p>\n<p><strong>Lead Magnets. </strong>A lead magnet is an incentive you offer your visitors in exchange for their email address. This could be a free PDF, an eBook, a report, and more.</p>\n<p><strong>Giveaways</strong>. Ask for someone&#8217;s email address as an entry. You can give them extra entries when they share your giveaway on social media.</p>\n<p><strong>Create A Poll. </strong>Get your visitors engaged and ask for their email in the process. WPForms lets you easily create engaging content with our <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-the-new-wpforms-surveys-and-polls-addon/\">Surveys and Polls Addon.</a> To start setting up polls on your website, read our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/good-poll-questions-to-ask-on-your-forms-for-better-feedback/\">good poll questions to ask on your forms for better feedback</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Offer a Coupon. </strong>An excellent option if you&#8217;re an eCommerce business. Not to mention coupons are a popular example of a lead magnet.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-434559\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/email-list-lead-magnet-popup.jpg\" alt=\"email-list-lead-magnet-popup\" width=\"562\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/email-list-lead-magnet-popup.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/email-list-lead-magnet-popup-300x186.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Which ways you choose to grow your email list will depend on the type of business you have.</p>\n<p>Lead magnets are popular because they can be used for almost anything. Ready to get more email subscribers and build a massive email list? Check out this great guide on <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/9-lead-magnets-to-increase-subscribers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">effective lead magnets to grow your email list</a> on our sister site.</p>\n<h3>How Do I Choose the Best Email Marketing Service?</h3>\n<p>A lot of people ask how big should my email list be. Some believe that the bigger, the better.</p>\n<p>However, while you want to focus on list building and grow your list to as many people as possible, your email list&#8217;s engagement is much more important. That&#8217;s why having a great email marketing service is so important.</p>\n<p>There are a lot of awesome email marketing providers. Since it&#8217;s a competitive field, a lot of them offer great features for low-cost.</p>\n<p>Two of our favorites that we&#8217;ve used and recommend are:</p>\n<p><strong>Constant Constant</strong></p>\n<p>Constant Contact is easily the very best email marketing service provider for all sizes of websites and businesses. They&#8217;re one of the largest email marketing services in the world for good reason. You can:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage Your Subscribers</li>\n<li>Send and Track Emails</li>\n<li>View Analytics</li>\n<li>Split Test Campaigns</li>\n<li>Target Subscribers</li>\n<li>Connect to <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-434673 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-logo.jpg\" alt=\"constant-contact-logo\" width=\"562\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-logo.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/constant-contact-logo-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Constant Contact is great because <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">it&#8217;s free to try</a>. You can setup your email list and start getting email addresses during your trial. By the end of the free period, your list will already be paying for itself.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s optional to pay after the trial period, so setup and start building your email list with <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> today.</p>\n<p><strong>Drip</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a> is a fantastic email marketing service provider. It lets you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage Your Subscribers</li>\n<li>Send and Track Emails</li>\n<li>View Detailed Reports</li>\n<li>Target Subscribers</li>\n<li>Setup Shareable Workflows and Automation</li>\n<li>Integrate with <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-434675 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drip-logo.jpg\" alt=\"drip-logo\" width=\"562\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drip-logo.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/drip-logo-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Not to mention, Drip lets you setup and start building an email list with a free plan that holds up to 100 emails. It&#8217;s a popular choice for many website owners. You can start building your email list with <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a> right away.</p>\n<p>Both Constant Contact and Drip work with WPForms. Get started setting up a <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">simple contact form</a> right now to see how it works.</p>\n<h3>What About Free Email Marketing Services?</h3>\n<p>We always recommend using a professional email marketing service like Constant Contact or Drip over free ones. It&#8217;s true that they cost money, but above all they&#8217;re an investment in your business with big returns.</p>\n<p>In addition, here are some of the downsides of using some free platforms:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can&#8217;t target specific subscribers by interests or demographics.</li>\n<li>There&#8217;s no reporting so you can&#8217;t tell which percentage of subscribers opened your email and visited your site.</li>\n<li>There&#8217;s little email customization.</li>\n<li>If you try to move to a paid service, your users will have to re-confirm. Many won&#8217;t, so you&#8217;ll lose subscribers.</li>\n<li>You can&#8217;t run A/B split tests to see which subject line and offers work best for your users.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In conclusion, it&#8217;s just a smart move to use a professional email marketing service like <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> or <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/drip/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Drip</a> if you&#8217;re a small business or entrepreneur.</p>\n<p>And there you have it! You now know why building an email list right away is so important for your website and business. You can easily get visitors to keeping coming back to your site and grow your revenue.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking to grow your small business online, be sure to check out these <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/online-form-statistics-facts/\">unbelievable online form statistics and facts</a> that can help you get the results you want.</p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget, if you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/why-you-should-start-building-an-email-list/\">Why You Should Start Building an Email List Right Away in 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wpforms.com/why-you-should-start-building-an-email-list/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"Introducing WPForms 1.5.2 – NEW Checkbox Limits + Smart Email &amp; Phone Fields\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 16 Apr 2019 14:39:43 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Announcement\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"lead generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"checkboxes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"phone fields\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=443706\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:573:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WPForms 1.5.2 is here! There are some new features in this release that pack a big punch and will make using WPForms even easier. Your form fields are about to get a lot smarter so you can get higher quality leads. Plus, Checkbox fields are going to make it even [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/\">Introducing WPForms 1.5.2 &#8211; NEW Checkbox Limits + Smart Email &#038; Phone Fields</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7934:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WPForms 1.5.2 is here!</p>\n<p>There are some new features in this release that pack a big punch and will make using WPForms even easier.</p>\n<p>Your form fields are about to get a lot smarter so you can get higher quality leads. Plus, Checkbox fields are going to make it even easier to segment and convert visitors into paying customers.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s what&#8217;s new in WPForms 1.5.2.</p>\n<h3>Phone Fields Now Auto-Detect Country Codes</h3>\n<p>The Phone field in your forms just got a super helpful revamp.</p>\n<p>The new Smart Phone feature auto-detects your user&#8217;s region as the form is loading. The Phone field will now show which region the person filling out the form is currently located in.</p>\n<p>If a user starts to type in a phone number format that&#8217;s different from the auto-detected format, a message will appear.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443888\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-message-wrong-format.jpg\" alt=\"form-message-wrong-format\" width=\"562\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-message-wrong-format.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/form-message-wrong-format-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /><br />\nAnd, it&#8217;s really easy for the user to change the auto-detected region on the Phone field.</p>\n<p>For example, say someone from India is visiting the US. The form will auto-detect that they are in the US and add the US phone number format to the Phone field.</p>\n<p>But, let&#8217;s also say that the user wants to enter their phone number which is from India, not the US.</p>\n<p>To do this, they can simply select a different region from the dropdown menu inside the Phone field.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443880\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dropdown-region-select.jpg\" alt=\"dropdown-region-select\" width=\"562\" height=\"301\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dropdown-region-select.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dropdown-region-select-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>If your business gets form entries from multiple regions, you&#8217;ll especially love this Smart Phone feature. We also created this new feature so that international users can now get validation when entering their number, not just US users.</p>\n<p>The Smart Phone feature will help you manage your form entries and keep phone numbers consistent and accurate. And, you&#8217;ll end up with higher quality leads.</p>\n<p>Head over to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-choose-the-right-form-field-for-your-forms/#phone\">how to choose the right form field for your forms</a> to learn more about the different phone formats.</p>\n<h3>Get More Leads With Email Address Typo Detection</h3>\n<p>The Email Field now has an exciting new feature you&#8217;ll love.</p>\n<p>The Smart Email feature spots typos in common domain names. The Email field will now display a message suggesting a fix if a user types in their email address wrong.</p>\n<p>For example, if someone types in liz@gmaill.com or liz@gnail.com, they&#8217;ll see a message with a suggestion of the proper spelling. They can click on the suggestion and the email address will be automatically fixed.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443895\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/smart-email-feature.jpg\" alt=\"smart-email-feature\" width=\"562\" height=\"311\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/smart-email-feature.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/smart-email-feature-300x166.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /><br />\nThe Smart Email feature works with 30 popular email service domains.</p>\n<p>We created the Smart Email feature because we know how important <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/beginners-guide-to-email-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">email marketing</a> is to small business owners and website builders.</p>\n<p>Because of this, we wanted to help make the form entries you receive as accurate as possible. That way, you can focus on building your email list, not fixing it.</p>\n<p>The Smart Email feature is going to help you capture <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-lead-generation-plugins-to-grow-your-email-list/\">higher quality leads</a>, <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/12-tips-to-reduce-bounce-rate-and-boost-your-conversions/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">reduce bounces</a>, and get more <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-track-wordpress-form-conversions-step-by-step/\">conversions</a> by spotting common email domain typos right away and helping correct them.</p>\n<h3>Limit the Number of Checkboxes Users Can Select</h3>\n<p>The new Checkbox Total Limits feature lets you limit how many checkboxes users can pick on your form. We&#8217;re really excited about this great new option and think you will be too!</p>\n<p>Before, it was difficult to limit checkbox totals on a form. For instance, say your form had 10 dog breeds listed and you asked people to pick their 3 favorite. Users could&#8217;ve ignored your request and selected all 10 dog breeds!</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s why we made Checkbox Total Limits. It&#8217;s now easier than ever to build and manage different <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/insanely-easy-ways-to-grow-your-email-list-fast-starting-now/\">email lists</a> based on your visitor&#8217;s individual preferences.</p>\n<p>If a user tries to select more checkboxes than your set limit, the form will tell them they&#8217;ve exceeded the number of allowed selections.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443921\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/checkbox-total-limit-message.jpg\" alt=\"checkbox-total-limit-message\" width=\"562\" height=\"453\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/checkbox-total-limit-message.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/checkbox-total-limit-message-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, the form won&#8217;t let them submit until that&#8217;s corrected.</p>\n<p>To set or change the Checkbox Total Limit in your Checkbox Field Options, simply click on Advanced Options and enter your desired numerical limit in the Choice Limit box. For a more in-depth look, check out our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-limit-the-number-of-checkboxes-selections/\">how to limit the number of checkboxes selections.</a></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-443726\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms\" width=\"562\" height=\"516\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-to-edit-checkbox-total-limit-wpforms-300x275.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And that covers the newest release!</p>\n<p>We think you&#8217;ll agree that WPForms is smarter and simpler than ever before.</p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for?</p>\n<p>Give the newest version of WPForms a try and let us know what you think about all the new updates.</p>\n<p>As always, thank you for your continued support of WPForms. We look forward to helping you succeed with your website and business.</p>\n<p><em>Lisa and the WPForms team</em></p>\n<p>P.S. Don’t have a WPForms Pro license? <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">Click here to get started today</a> and experience the WPForms difference.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/\">Introducing WPForms 1.5.2 &#8211; NEW Checkbox Limits + Smart Email &#038; Phone Fields</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wpforms.com/introducing-wpforms-1-5-2/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\"